title: fritters
directions: Stir milk into well beaten eggs; add flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in fat and mix until well blended.
Dip fruit, vegetables or meat into fritter batter.
Drop into hot deep fat (375°) and fry until golden brown.
Drain and serve hot.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Cut wings into 3 pieces.

Simmer tips in broth, catsup, soy sauce, sugar and vinegar for sauce. Beat egg, water and oil. Dip wings in egg mixture. Drain on rack and sprinkle both sides with cornstarch. Heat oil and garlic to 350°.
Add wings and brown on both sides.
Place wings in large flat baking dish and add sauce mixture. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: beaver houses(no bake cookies)
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Stir in rest of ingredients and drop with a spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool and eat.

title: swiss vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 4 ounces Swiss cheese, sour cream, pimento and half of dressing mix and 1/2 can onions.
Season to taste.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish and bake covered 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining dressing mix, cheese and onion.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes longer.

title: zenda's russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 1 teaspoon per glass or cupful. This is very good used for making hot tea.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Mix butter, stuffing and water or stock.
Add cream of chicken soup and mix well.
Add diced chicken.
Put in an 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake for another 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 30 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute by hand.
Pour into plate.

title: chili dressing
directions: In a bowl, combine vinegar, salt, chili powder, pepper and garlic.
Add chili sauce.
Stir to combine.
Finally, add oil and blend well.

title: country ham
directions: Soak ham overnight in lard tin (14 to 15 pounds) with 1 cup Grandma's molasses and 1 cup vinegar.
Next morning, remove ham from lard tin; rinse good and rinse can.
Put ham back in lard tin with rack in bottom so meat won't stick to bottom of it.
Mix 1 cup Grandma's molasses and 1 cup vinegar and pour over ham.
Fill lard tin with water to cover ham, leaving space on top to boil. Put top on lard tin and put on stove.
Put on high heat until it starts to a hard boil.
Start to time for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and cut cauliflower into bite-sized pieces.
Finely chop onion.
Mix all ingredients and chill at least 1 hour.
This will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: portuguese beans
directions: Soak beans overnight with 2 to 2 1/2-quarts of water. Cook in a covered pot on low heat until almost done. Cut bacon and onions into small pieces.
Brown separately. Drain well and add to beans. Add remaining ingredients. Continue to cook on low heat 3 to 4 hours.
If a more thickened sauce is desired, remove lid and increase heat for awhile.
Makes 3 to 4 quarts.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Slice sausage; saute with onion until tender.
Drain off fat. Stir in apples, sauerkraut, water, brown sugar and caraway seed. Blend well.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: frosted orange salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Drain pineapple (save juice) and add to gelatin. Add cold water and bananas. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 dish coated with nonstick spray.

title: lil's lefse
directions: Bring to boil water, margarine, sugar and salt.
Remove from heat and add milk.
Add instant potatoes and stir.
Cover and store in refrigerator until thoroughly cooled; overnight is good.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Bake cake in square cake pan.
When done, prick top with toothpick.
Mix sugar and pineapple and bring to boil until dissolved; pour over cake.
Cook pudding as directed and pour over pineapple mixture.
Spread whipped cream over pudding and sprinkle with coconut.

title: crustless buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients together with an electric mixer.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: impossible triple cheese pie
directions: The pie that does the impossible by making its own crust.

title: new york roast beef
directions: Rub oil over entire surface of meat.
Combine remaining ingredients; rub over
roast.
Place
meat	in
shallow baking dish with fat side up.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes per pound. The result will be a brown outer surface with an even rareness in the middle.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Blend the egg whites until foamy/frothy. Blend the cream of tartar, salt and sugar into whites. Tint with food coloring if desired. Add any type of flavoring desired. Pipe into shapes. Bake on baking sheet with parchment paper at 200° for 3 hours. May take several baking sheets, but bake all at the same time.

title: crescent cinnamon twirls
directions: Use 1/2
package
(4) rolls.
Do not separate; open out and press
lines
together.
Combine
brown
sugar
and
soft margarine to cinnamon.
Spread
on top of first 4 rolls.
Open and place remaining 4 rolls on top; press lines together.
Cut in half long
way,	then
in small strips (about finger size). Twist and place
on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken into 3-inch strips.
In large skillet cook chicken in oil over high heat until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice. Cover and simmer an additional 10 minutes or until rice is tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses and mix with mixer until blended, then add garlic powder.
Place this mixture in the refrigerator until it hardens.
Roll into balls (2) and then roll into chopped nuts and parsley flakes that have been mixed thoroughly together.
Can be frozen until needed.

title: pecan cheese log
directions: Grate cheese; blend with soft cheese, garlic and pecans.
Roll in paprika on waxed paper.
Shape into log; chill.
Slice thin and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: banana poppy seed muffins
directions: Microwave butter and brown sugar on High to a boil, then on High 2 to 3 minutes to form a syrup.
Pour 1/2 the syrup and 1/2 pecans into ovenproof Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Stand biscuits on edge around pan (inside), then add the remaining syrup and pecans between biscuits and over top.
Bake 25 minutes on Low.
Then invert immediately onto plate after cooked!

title: chewy bread
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Then pour brown sugar into bowl and oleo over sugar.
Mix well and add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Beat the eggs, molasses, sugar, lard then add dry ingredients. Make a ball size of fifty-cent piece and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Don't flatten the balls.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Saute onion, celery, garlic and oil in a large pot.

Cook until tender, about 10 minutes. Add tomatoes, water, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Add beans, pasta and parsley. Cover and cook until pasta is tender. Serve in soup bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve with Italian crust bread and a big green salad.
Enjoy.

title: summer coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, honey, salt and pepper.
Stir in cabbage until coated with mayonnaise mixture. Saving about 1 tablespoon carrots, stir in remaining carrots into coleslaw.
Transfer coleslaw to serving dish; top with reserved carrots.
Serves 8.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Add broth and soup over the chicken.
Melt margarine.
Add pepper, milk and flour.
Pour this over the chicken mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir together sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Fold in whipped Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mama dodo's potato soup
directions: In a large soup kettle, saute onions in olive oil; add flour to make a light roux.
Add water.
Bring to a boil and cook until smooth.
Add celery, carrots, potatoes and paprika; bring to a boil again.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: spice cookies
directions: Combine in large mixer bowl at low speed for 1 minute. Gradually add 2 1/4 cups flour.
Blend at low speed just until stiff dough forms, about 1 minute.
Roll out 1/3 of dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter and bake at 375°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, vanilla, Karo syrup and butter. Lay pecans on bottom of pie pastry.
Add mixture and bake 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: really good, really easy carrots
directions: Cook carrots until fork-tender (do not overcook).
Cook sugar, butter and orange juice until syrupy.
Pour over carrots and mix lightly.
Serve hot.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add half the condensed milk; blend.
Pour half the batter into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish that has been well sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Fry fatback in large frypan; remove.
Add fryer; brown on all sides.
Sprinkle with flour, coating and browning both sides. Stir in water slowly; sprinkle with onion, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover with tight fitting lid and cook on medium-low heat until gravy boils 10 minutes.
Reduce to low heat; cover. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt the margarine; add 10x sugar, vanilla and cocoa, then peanut butter.
Mix all together and roll into small balls.
Roll in coconut.
Lay balls on a cookie sheet.
Cover with foil.
Put in freezer.
After frozen, put in plastic bags.
Freeze until ready to eat.

title: gram's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on until soft. Chop all other ingredients and mix into mayonnaise. Peel and slice potatoes while still hot. Add to mayonnaise mixture and stir well.
Add salt and pepper. Chill overnight.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Put fruit in the bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg.
In a small saucepan, melt the margarine.
Put the crumb mixture over top of apples. Drizzle the melted margarine over the crumbs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream banana bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir remaining ingredients in order listed.
Mix well and spread in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan and spread with glaze.
Cut into 48 bars.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine milk, pumpkin, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top.
Melt oleo and drizzle over top of cake mix. Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: banana salad
directions: Take fresh bananas, slice in rounds.
Add chopped walnuts. Mix powdered sugar and mayonnaise until smooth.
Toss together as a salad.

title: taco pie
directions: Bake pie shells at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Brown meat and onion.
Add taco mix.
In a small bowl, mix beans and sauce.

title: summer fruit delight
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and stir contents. Place in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: poor boy chicken
directions: Wash
meat in cold water to remove salt. Slice 1/4-inch thick, or thicker if desired.
Soak in cold water over night. Mix
white meal
and	black pepper, sufficient amount to meal down
the meat.
Pat meal into the meat.
Put meat in skillet on
medium fire with the cooking oil.	Let this fry until dark golden brown, turning from side to side two or three times.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Put all ingredients in pot and cook until veggies are done. Cool and skim off fat from beef.
Eat and enjoy.

title: cool cucumber salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cucumber, tomato, green pepper, and onion. In a small bowl, combine vinegar, dill, salt, and pepper. Pour over cucumber mixture; toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 15 minutes. Serve with slotted spoon.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter; stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without further stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popped corn in a large bowl, mixing well with a fork.
Turn into 2 large shallow baking pans.
Bake for 1 hour in 250° oven, stirring every 15 minutes.
Set pans out of oven; cool completely.
Break apart.
Store in airtight containers.

title: old fashioned vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan. Gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 20 minutes. Beat eggs and gradually stir some of the hot mixture into the eggs. Add egg mixture to remaining hot mixture. Add Eagle Brand milk and vanilla, stirring constantly. Cook about 5 minutes longer and strain into freezer. (This removes any egg that is lumpy.) Finish filling the freezer with milk and chill overnight. Freeze as directed.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together like a cake.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.

title: snowball (wedding dough) cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine flour, nuts, granulated sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often until well mixed.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake for 18 to 25 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Remove immediately.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm and again when cool.
Makes about three dozen.

title: my great grandmother's christmas cookies
directions: Cream lard, butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, buttermilk, baking powder, vanilla, salt and enough flour to make it dough. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: louisiana meat pie
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet.
Stir in beans, soup and seasonings.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with second shell and seal edges.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: lake margaret hot cinnamon apples
directions: Combine apple pie filling and sugar and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Place in casserole dish and mix brown sugar and butter or margarine.
Cover top of apples with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: morning mix ups
directions: In skillet saute onion and ham.
Add potatoes, cook until potatoes are tender.
Add beaten eggs, salt and pepper.
Scramble. Serve with toast and fruit.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: *One 10 ounce package frozen strawberries (partially thawed) may be substituted.
Then reduce sugar to 2/3 cup.

title: crunchy oven fried chicken
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well. Coat chicken with yogurt mixture and dredge in cereal.
Place chicken on a rack in a roasting pan coated with cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.. Makes 4 servings.
Cal. 240, total fat 3, cholesterol 75 mg., sodium 223 mg.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix and drop
by
teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until brown around edge only.

title: jan metcalf's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in oats; mix.
Form dough in rolls 1 to 1 1/2-inch diameter. Wrap in waxed paper; chill.
Slice cookies 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: marinated shrimp and vegetables
directions: Place shrimp and vegetables in shallow dish.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except oil.
Mix well.
Add oil; mix well.
Pour over shrimp and vegetables.
Cover; refrigerate 6 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes about 5 cups.

title: easy ice cream brownies
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine together until crumbly.
Press mixture into the bottom of a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square cake pan.
Spoon soft ice cream over the top.
Nuts can be sprinkled over the top, if desired.
Place in freezer; cut into squares when serving.
Fudge or caramel topping can be added when served.
Any flavor of ice cream can be used.

title: italian ribs
directions: Cover ribs in Italian dressing.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour. Sprinkle garlic salt, lemon pepper and cayenne pepper on both sides of ribs. Dust lightly with chili pepper. Cook in oven for 1 hour at 250°.
Then add 1 slice of Cheddar cheese per rib. Cook 15 minutes more at 350° or until done.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; slowly add syrup, then eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Then add flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a sheet pan.
If put in a glass 13 x 9-inch cake pan, bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: south georgia corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix together with other ingredients. Beat
well	by
hand.
Pour
into oiled iron skillet or muffin pan.
Bake	at
approximately 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken simplicity
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and mix soup, mushrooms, almonds and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with paprika. Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Uncover and allow to brown about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a small bowl, add enough salsa to refried beans so it can be easily spread on serving platter. Set mixture aside.

title: irish coffee dessert
directions: In a 5 cup blender or food processor, sprinkle unflavored gelatin over cold milk and let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Add hot milk and process at low speed until gelatin is dissolved (about 2 minutes).
Add sugar, coffee powder, whiskey and creme de cacao. Process at high speed.
Add ice cubes 1 at a time until melted. Pour into Irish coffee mugs or dessert dishes.
Chill until set.

title: sweet potatoes and bananas
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cover with water and bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook 15 to 20 minutes, until tender.
Drain.
Peel and cube bananas.
Toss bananas with lemon juice.
Mash bananas and potatoes and put into pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, nutmeg and salt.
Drizzle with rum and butter.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: gringo chili(lo-fat)
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, cook turkey, onion and garlic over medium heat until turkey loses its pink color.
Drain fat. Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Melt 2 cheeses in top of double boiler.
Add soup and frozen broccoli.
Stir until all is melted. Serve warm with chips or veggies.
Sauteed onions are good to add to this dip.

title: tropical chicken(method:  foil)
directions: Brush the chicken with butter on both sides; sprinkle with salt.
Mix remaining butter and soy sauce.
Place the chickens on grill; cook over low coals for 20 to 25 minutes on each side, brushing frequently with butter mix.
Place each chicken half on a large piece of foil; place a banana half on each side of chicken pieces.
Place equal amounts of fruits on top of banana and around each piece of chicken.
Sprinkle each piece with cinnamon; top each with a green pepper slice.
Wrap tightly; return to grill for 10 to 15 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix soups, milk, chiles, onion, seasonings and hamburger in large bowl.
Cut tortillas into wedges.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer tortillas and meat mixture two or three times.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: easy eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut up into squares.	Chop onion. Cut up pepper into bite-size. Mix all together in dish.

Mix together tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste and minced garlic depending on how much you like. Pour over vegetables and drizzle with olive oil. Cook at 350° for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Can be served hot or cold.

title: spinach artichoke casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichoke hearts and cut into quarters.
Arrange on the bottom of a buttered casserole dish. Squeeze water out of defrosted spinach and mix spinach with the soup.
Spread over artichokes.
Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread over the top.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: good good cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake according to directions on box.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done, punch holes in top of cake with a wooden handle.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk over the top of cake, then pour caramel sauce over that.
Crush the Heath bars and crumble over the top of cake.
Let get cold.
Then put Cool Whip on the top.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Make small balls, size of walnuts (can be smaller for bite
size
goodies).
Fry.
(Or
bake	in 350° oven on cookie sheet until done to your liking.)

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix and roll in small balls.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs just enough to blend evenly.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Add slowly, beating with a fork, the scalded milk and vanilla.
Place in a greased Pyrex dish and sprinkle with grated nutmeg.
Set bowl in a pan of hot water, lined with brown paper. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: banana-nana-cake
directions: Mix together in the order as mentioned.
Start with shortening, salt and so on.
Grease and flour cake pans.
Fill pans half full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or in an oblong pan for 50 minutes.

title: dreamsicle salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O into thawed Cool Whip, stirring well, until all Jell-O has dissolved.
Fold in drained pineapple and cottage cheese.
Chill well and enjoy.

title: company chicken
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and cooking sherry.
Pour over chicken breasts and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: grandma's chicken
directions: Put croutons in milk and let it soak up the milk, making a pastry spread.

title: cheesy baked ziti and vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook ziti according to directions. Meanwhile, prepare white sauce:
In medium size saucepan over low heat, melt margarine; remove from heat.
Stir in flour, mustard, salt and pepper until smooth.
Slowly stir in milk; return to heat until thickened.
Stir in half of the cheese, low heat until melted.
Drain pasta; stir in sauce.
Stir in scallions, broccoli, zucchini and tomato; mix well.
Into 2-quart baking dish, pour pasta and vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake for 20 minutes until bubbly and top slightly crusty golden.
Makes 4 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and peel.
Slice into casserole dish.
In frying pan, fry bacon until crispy.
Pull out bacon and put on paper towel.
In bacon grease, add chopped onion, sugar and vinegar. Add flour and bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes and break bacon up over.
Mix together and serve warm.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Blend butter, cream cheese, onion and lemon juice with shrimp. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over pineapple; bring to a strong boil, stirring constantly. Cool. Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Fold in pineapple mixture. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in bowl with mixer.
Add the peanut butter.
Mix, then make into balls.
Put on wax paper and put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
In a saucepan, melt the shortening and chocolate chips.
Put chocolate on balls. Refrigerate for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: low-fat blueberry bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 12 muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray or line with paper baking cups.
Set aside.

title: baked carrots
directions: Pare carrots; put in casserole.
Cream the butter, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add boiling water; blend well.
Pour over carrots. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased baking dish. Decorate with green pepper strips and pimento strips and Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered at 375°.

title: crabmeat imperial
directions: In large skillet on low heat, melt margarine.
Add green onion; cook until softened.
Add mushrooms and heat about 5 minutes.
Add crabmeat, pimiento and sherry.
Break apart any large lumps of crabmeat and heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve on toast points or pasta.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Cut up candy bars in small pieces.
Slice cake in half.
Tear 1/2 of cake into bite size pieces and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Combine Cool Whip, margarine, sugar and egg yolks; mix well.
Layer half of this over cake pieces.
Sprinkle half of candy over this.
Repeat layers again.
Best if left overnight in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt together in heavy pan peanut butter and butter until just melted.
Pour into large bowl.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add box of sugar; knead together.

title: pork chops -- oriental flavor
directions: Season both sides of the chops with the seasoning blend and pepper. In a large nonstick skillet, brown chops in margarine on each side over medium heat. Add tea, celery, onion and soy sauce and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, until meat is tender. Remove meat to serving platter. Drain liquid, reserving vegetables, placing them on platter with meat.

title: fruit and lettuce salad
directions: Stir together lettuce, bananas, apples, maraschino cherries and walnuts.
Mix equal amounts of sour cream and salad dressing together.
Thin with milk or cream and sweeten to taste.
Mix or toss together.
Keeps well.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Add onion to warm potatoes.
Stir flour into bacon drippings in a large frypan.
Add sugar, butter, salt, pepper, water and vinegar; bring to a boil, stir constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Add potatoes, onion and half the bacon; toss gently.
Turn into a heated salad bowl.
Garnish with the remaining bacon and parsley sprigs.

title: haystacks
directions: Heat sugar and Karo to barely boiling. Add brown sugar, barely boiling again, beat. Remove from heat, beat and let cool. Then reheat to boiling point and set off heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Pour over cereal and coconut, which has been mixed. Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper, cool.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients together until pecans are coated. Set aside!

title: hush puppies
directions: Add oleo to dry ingredients, then pour in boiling water.
Mix well and roll into hush puppies.
Yields 50 to 60 hush puppies. Freezes well.

title: reese cups made into egg shapes
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Mix in other two ingredients. Shape into eggs.
Dip in melted chocolate if desired.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan. Combine butter and cocoa in a medium-sized, heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, egg, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth. Spread batter evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until center feels dry.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle marshmallows, walnuts and chocolate chips over the top.
Return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes or just until topping is warm enough to melt together. Let cool; then cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: company chicken
directions: Lay chicken in a greased 9 x 13 glass dish. Add other ingredients in order given. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Also can be prepared a day ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: brownie almond torte
directions: Up to one week before serving, preheat oven to 350°.
In double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream margarine with sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
At low speed, beat in chocolate, vanilla, flour mixture and almonds.
Grease cookie sheet.
Place 1 or 2 waxed paper circles on it.
Grease circles.
Spread 1/2 cup batter on paper making it even and round.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Remove.
Cool.
Remove paper.
Continue baking layers.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice the tomatoes 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick and season them with salt and pepper. Spread the flour or cornmeal on a baking sheet and add the tomato slices, coating each side evenly. Melt the butter in a heavy skillet; when very hot, add the slices in a single layer, but do not crowd. When golden brown, turn and brown the second side. Drain on paper towels. Proceed in batches until all are done. Serve with marinara sauce, if desired. Yield:
4 servings.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or with mixer.
Place in glass jar and add garlic.
If dry mustard is used in blender, it will be thicker.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together
dry ingredients.
Beat eggs;
add water, pumpkin and oil.
Stir
into
dry ingredients.
Add nuts last. Bake in a greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat; blend in milk.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in chocolate mixture; pour into pie shell.
Combine coconut and nuts; sprinkle on top of chocolate mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients and sweeten to taste.

title: easy swiss rye bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.

title: fried rice
directions: Cut and fry bacon. When done, drain off most of the grease. Add celery and onions. Saut until about half done. Add cooked rice and soy sauce to taste.

title: best chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: moist coffee chocolate chip brownies
directions: Add coffee to water. Mix everything together. Grease 9 x 13 pan. Top with nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Pierce chicken breasts with a fork. Combine all other ingredients in a small mixing bowl, mix well. Place chicken in a casserole dish and cover with mixture. Bake at 350F
for 20-25 minutes or until done.

title: smoked turkey pie
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients.
Spoon into baked pie shell. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot and cheese melts.

title: country vegetable soup(yield: 12 servings)
directions: Add soup bone to 2 quarts of water and boil for 10 minutes. Add vegetables and macaroni.
Cook until tender on simmer. Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup of bouillon.
Stir cornstarch mixture into vegetable mixture.
Add remainder of bouillon and simmer until stock thickens (approximately 1 hour).
Serve hot.

title: dressing for fruit
directions: Whip together.
Serve on fresh fruit or fruit salad.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Place in baking pan and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Set aside to cool. Dice apples. Mix in pineapple mixture.
Mix Cool Whip and salad dressing.
Spread apple mixture in dish (8 x 10-inch) and cover with Cool Whip mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Serves 12 people.

title: heath bar trifle
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed.
Cool.
Prepare pudding and milk according to package directions.
Break up half of cake in pieces and layer on bottom of glass bowl.
Pour 1/4 cup Kahlua over cake.
Layer with half of pudding and half of Cool Whip. Sprinkle 2 Heath bars over Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine zucchini, onion, soup, sour cream, carrots and cheese; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine margarine and stuffing mix.
Sprinkle half of stuffing mixture on bottom of 3-quart casserole.
Pour vegetable combination over the crumbs.
Pour remaining stuffing mixture on top.
Bake in preheated oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings. Delicious.

title: smoked sausage and cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in a large skillet; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add water to a depth of 1/2 to 1-inch.
Bring to a boil; add sausage.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until cabbage is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with cornbread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: seafood yummo
directions: Cut off crusts of bread and cut each slice into 24 cubes.
Put in large bowl with tight fitting cover.
Add chopped eggs and chopped onion.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
Next day, add 1 pint mayonnaise, chopped celery, shrimp and crabmeat. Refrigerate at least 3 hours; overnight is best.
Keeps well. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil Boston butt until tender.
Remove bones and chop meat. Place in a saucepan.
Add creamed corn, catsup, hot sauce and a small amount of the broth meat was cooked in.
Cook slowly for about 30 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Let congeal and top.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Let stand in fridge for 2 - 4 hours.
Serve with slice of lemon if desired. Very refreshing.

title: i can't stop eating party dip
directions: Pour salsa over cream cheese; serve with vegetable sticks and tortilla chips.
It is guaranteed that your guests will love it.

title: no sugar butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and gradually add honey.
Beat in egg yolk.
Add lemon peel, flour, baking powder and lemon juice.
Stir well. Chill dough.
Shape dough into small balls and arrange on greased cookie sheet.
Brush lightly with beaten egg white.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain 2 packages frozen chopped broccoli.
Place in a large Pyrex baking dish.
Top with 1 (4 oz.) can mushroom pieces. Saute onion in butter until soft; blend in flour and seasonings, then add milk and bouillon cubes and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Stir a little hot sauce into egg yolks, then return egg mixture to saucepan.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Spread sauce over broccoli.
Sprinkle with almonds and paprika.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
This makes a big casserole.
To serve a smaller group, divide broccoli into two pans, or extra sauce may be frozen.

title: magic wands
directions: You will also need ribbon.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onions in margarine for 10 minutes. Stir in parsley or parsley flakes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano leaves.
Combine eggs and Mozzarella.
Stir in zucchini mixture.
Separate dinner rolls.
Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until center is set.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients in baking dish.
Spray dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with squares of Italian bread.

title: country fried steak
directions: Sprinkle steaks with pepper lightly and cover with buttermilk. Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge each steak in flour until well coated.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together well.
Chill for 5 minutes in refrigerator.
Beat whipping cream until fluffy.
Fold into pudding mixture.
Slice bananas; dip in lemon juice.

title: quince honey
directions: Pare quince and
apples
and grate them.
Measure pulp. Measure 3/4 as much
sugar
as
pulp.
Pour boiling water over sugar and stir until sugar is almost dissolved.
Add the fruit pulp and lemon juice
and
cook
until mixture is clear.
Pour into clean hot jars and
cover
with paraffin.
It will be the appearance and consistency of honey.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown meat with onion and seasoning.
Drain liquid from beans. Put meat and beans in layers in greased 2-quart casserole; heat soup and milk and pour over mixture.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until heated in 350° oven.

title: chicken bog
directions: Add to chicken.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Cook until all water is absorbed.

title: angel delight
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, tear up angel food cake.
Make pudding as directed on box and add the vanilla.
When set, spread over angel food cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle candy pieces on top.

title: chicken wings and sweet and pungent sauce
directions: Cut tips from wings (put back for later broth).
Cut wings at joint.
Salt, pepper and flour, then fry.
Place all ingredients in a pan except cornstarch.
Bring to a boil and stir in cornstarch made into a paste with a little cold water.
Boil 1 minute.
(This sauce is better if made in advance and reheated before serving.) Pour sauce over fried wings.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: curried chicken salad with mangoes and almonds
directions: Whisk together mayonnaise, chicken broth, yogurt and curry powder until well blended.
Stir into the chicken until all pieces are coated.
Peel and slice the mango from its stone.
Cube the mango to about the size of the chicken pieces.
Gently stir into the chicken.

title: black beans(caracas, venezuela)
directions: Early in the spring, till your garden and lay into rows. After the last sign of frost, plant pinto beans (they must be pintos) in rows about 6 inches apart, then wait!

title: hot pepper rings
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with pepper rings. Beat eggs, milk and melted butter together and pour over pepper rings.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Slice and serve on Triscuits or crackers.

title: guacamole dip
directions: In a medium bowl or food processor, mash avocado.
Add sour cream, garlic powder, salt, lemon or lime juice, chilies and Tabasco sauce.
Blend well.
Stir in onion and tomato.
Serve immediately, or store in refrigerator with plastic wrap against surface of guacamole to prevent from turning brown.
Makes 2 about cups.

title: applesauce squares supreme
directions: Mix in order given except cherry juice, raisins and nuts, then add 1/3 cup maraschino juice and raisins and nuts.
For added variety, add chopped cherries.
Use greased angel food cake tin or pour mixture onto a large cake sheet, putting half a cherry every 3 inches apart (to be squared off after baking).
Bake about 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, oats and brown sugar in small bowl.
Stir in butter until mixture is crumbly; set aside.
Combine apples with sugar, remaining flour and cinnamon.
Place apple mixture in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumb topping over apple mixture. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: black bean dip
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Blend until smooth.
Adjust seasonings and amount of onions to your taste.
No fat; high fiber.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Make pudding with milk (I know package says 4 cups, but only use 3!), mix thoroughly with Cool Whip.
Line bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour in half of pudding mix; top with more crackers and repeat with other half of pudding mix and more crackers.
Frost with frosting.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onion in it.
Mix thoroughly the soups, onion and Ro-Tel. Place in dish by layers, Doritos, chicken and sauce. Repeat. Cover with cheese. Bake in medium 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: bean patties
directions: Cook beans; press through food mill while still hot or beat by hand until smooth.
Add all other ingredients and form into patties.
Roll in bread crumbs or wheat germ.
Fry in hot oil.
If you prefer, oil a baking pan with vegetables oil and bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until brown, turning once.
Serve hot and garnish as desired.

title: french apple pie cake
directions: Put apples in a buttered 9-inch deep pie plate.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over the apples.
Sift next 4 ingredients into a bowl.
Add last four ingredients and mix batter smooth.
Pour over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and set aside.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Using pastry blender blend margarine into flour until well blended.
Add milk and stir with fork until all flour is moistened. Scoop out onto floured surface.
Knead dough just enough to mix. Pat or roll to 1-inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits and place on baking sheet side by side.	Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until tops begin to turn slightly brown.	Then broil until desired browned on top.
Makes about 1 dozen biscuits.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute sausage for 5 to 10 minutes. Remove sausage but leave grease in skillet. Add the next 5 ingredients; saute 5 minutes and then add to crock-pot, including grease. Add the remaining ingredients to crock-pot and cook on low for 3 to 5 hours or until done. Serve over rice.

title: mom's foundation sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and the 1 tablespoon sugar in the lukewarm water.
Scald milk.
Let cool.
Add shortening, sugar and salt. When lukewarm, add 2 cups of the flour to this mixture.
Now add yeast and beaten eggs; beat well.
Add remaining flour, enough to make stiff dough.
Knead lightly and place in greased bowl.
Cover and set in warm place for about 2 hours or until almost doubled. Work out dough for dinner rolls or roll out for cinnamon rolls.

title: georgia bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, milks and egg yolks together thoroughly.
Add melted butter, raisins, vanilla and spices and mix well.
Add bread cubes to mixture and toss to saturate bread. Pour mixture into a buttered 8 x 8 inch baking dish and bake for 25 minutes until pudding is lightly browned and set.
Allow to cool before cutting.
It gets firmer and is easier to cut when cool.
Cut into squares and reheat slightly in the microwave before serving, if desired.
Yield 8 to 9 servings.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Chop lettuce; put in bottom of oblong dish preferrably Tupperware container.
Chop celery and onion together; spread over the lettuce.
Pour peas over celery and onion.
Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Spread grated cheese over mayonnaise.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: baked pork chops with rice
directions: Season the chops with salt and pepper; dredge them in flour. Brown on both sides in a small amount of fat.
Remove browned chops to a casserole.
Add soaked rice to the fat in the pan and cook, stirring frequently, until rice is lightly browned.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; set bowl aside. In a larger bowl, combine shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Mix until creamy.
You may add egg at this point.
Gradually add flour mixture in small bowl to the creamy mixture in large bowl. Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: danny's fruit cake
directions: Put pineapple in a 9 x 9-inch pan and put peaches and cherries on top.
The peaches and cherries are drained.
Pineapple is undrained.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit and then the nuts.
Cut butter in small slices and layer over cake mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add water to make a stiff dough.
Mix well.
Boil or steam for 4 hours.
Grandma always uses more raisins.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on tortillas fairly thin.
Roll tortillas as small as possible, like a jelly roll. Chill overnight and cut in bite size pieces.
Dip in picante sauce.
Can also use a layer of refried beans on top of cheese mixture.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan. Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and stir in jello.
Fill baked pie shell with 4 cups strawberries and pour mixture over berries. Chill for several hours.
Top with whipped topping before serving.

title: rhodes bread cinnamon rolls
directions: When dough is thawed, make into little balls.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or use a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/8 cup water.
Put on top a mixture of the pudding, brown sugar, melted margarine, cinnamon and pecans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: julie's taco pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients together.
Layer tortilla and cheese with beef mixture, bottom layer ground beef mixture, top most layer being cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Use 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients together until incorporated; do not overmix (lumps are okay).
Drop tablespoons at a time into pan with 1/4 inch of oil; do not crowd.
Cook until golden brown on both sides. Dust with powdered sugar.
Serve immediately.

title: homemade butter
directions: Soften margarine to room temperature.
Beat with mixer while adding buttermilk, 1 cup at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Put in plastic bowls and freeze.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Beat butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Fold in dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk.
Add raisins and vanilla.
Pour into greased pans and bake until golden brown.
Cut a cross with the back of a fork across the top of the loaf before baking to prevent cracking.
Bake in 350° oven.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour for 2 loaf pans or bake about 40 minutes for 3 smaller pans.

title: green chile chicken casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter in skillet; set aside. Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Heat well.
Layer large casserole dish with crushed Doritos (save some to set around edge of dish).
Put chicken (cut into chunks), mushrooms, pimentos and green chiles over Doritos.
Pour the heated soups over all and top with the American cheese first, then the Mozzarella cheese.
Put in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well; form into one or two loaves.
Cover with sauce and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon chiffon
directions: In a small pan, sprinkle Jell-O onto the warm water and leave spongy.
Beat egg yolks and sugar with electric beater until very light and fluffy (about 5 minutes).
Stir in the lemon rind, juice and half and half.
Melt the spongy Jell-O over low heat, stirring constantly; stir into the yolk mixture.
Cool the lemon mixture until it is just on the point of setting.
Stiffly beat the egg whites and fold into the mixture into a serving bowl and put into refrigerator until set (about 1 hour).

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook the eggplant and when it is done, drain the water off. Put eggplant in large bowl.
Beat together 1 teaspoon salt, 2 eggs and 1 cup milk.
Put this mixture in the bowl with eggplant.
Add the next four ingredients to eggplant and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: corn with bacon and caramelized onion
directions: Cut corn from cob. Set aside. Cook bacon in heavy skillet until crisp. Save 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside. Add thin sliced onion to drippings in skillet. Cook over medium heat, stirring often, for 15 minutes or until onion is caramel colored. Add corn and cook for 8 minutes, stirring often. Stir in molasses, salt and pepper. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Combine everything except butter.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add butter and beat to desired consistency.

title: butter crunch chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients with hands.
Spread in oblong pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Take from oven and stir.
Press 2 cups hot butter crunch against bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Boil hen until tender.
Save stock.
Dice the chicken and measure by cupfuls.
Brown the flour in the butter and stir the broth to make brown gravy.
Add onion.
Season to taste with pepper and soy sauce.
Drain Chinese vegetables and mix with chicken.
Gradually stir in the onion gravy until mixture has the consistency of hash.
Reserve any extra gravy to serve in gravy bowl.
Serve chow mein hot over rice.
Garnish with toasted almonds and green olives.
Serves 10.

title: microwave beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix all together and microwave on High for 20 minutes.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Roll in small balls and chill.
Dip in 2 cups melted chocolate.
(Make chocolate mixture of 12 ounces semi-sweet chocolate chips and 1/3 square of paraffin melted together in top of double boiler.)

title: christmas salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Heat juice from fruit and add Jell-O.
Dissolve thoroughly.
Chill until syrupy and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into long Pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.

title: bran muffins
directions: Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: herb crumb crusted chicken
directions: In a large glass dish, marinate chicken in butter, parsley, scallions, mushrooms, chives, salt and pepper for 1 hour at room temperature or several hours in the refrigerator.
If refrigerated allow chicken to return to room temperature.
Heavily coat each piece of chicken with bread crumbs and bake in a preheated 375° oven for about 30 minutes or until golden, crunchy and done. Serves 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, salt, flour, chocolate and cornstarch. Mix well before adding milk to mixture.
Add milk and cook on medium heat, stirring constantly.
After mixture heats through, add cup of mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Then return to pan and cook until smooth and thick.
Remove from stove, add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue, beaten well.
Bake in 325° oven until brown.

title: best apple pie
directions: Makes 2 single pie shells for a 10-inch pie pan.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Measure sugar, salt, shortening and 1 1/2 cups warm water in large bowl.
Beat in yeast and eggs.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough and mix well.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down, cover tightly and refrigerate.
Remove dough from refrigerator. Shape rolls and let rise, about 45 minutes.
Bake in preheated 400 degree oven for 15-20 minutes, or until golden.
Brush tops with butter.
Dough will keep 3-4 days in refrigerator.

title: candied yams and apples
directions: Combine apples and yams; pour into shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon over entire casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa and salt; set aside.
Add sugar gradually to Crisco, creaming well.
Blend in the unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine soda with milk; add gradually to creamed mixture, beating well.
Add dry ingredients all at once.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in boiling water until blended.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes (15 minutes for cupcakes).
Do not overbake as this is a moist cake.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Mix together and marinate with dressing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Brown onion in butter; dissolve flour in water and stir until thickened.
Add cheese and beaten eggs; stir in broccoli.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cake
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans until coarse.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: grape jelly
directions: Place the frozen grape juice and water in a large pan.
Add the Sure-Jell.
Add the oleo, which helps keep it from boiling too high.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Add the sugar; stir and bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Skim foam off; pour into jars.
Makes about 3 1/2 pints.

title: pennsylvania hot pot
directions: Place tenderloin in a kettle and add water, cider, sugar and vinegar.
Cover and simmer gently until tenderloin is tender or about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove tenderloin and place vegetables and apples into liquid.
Sprinkle vegetables with salt and pepper.
Cut tenderloin into 1/2-inch thick crosswise slices.
Place slices on top of vegetables.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve with mustard and horseradish.

title: famous cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a bowl, mix together Bisquick, milk and cheese.
Mix together until forms a soft dough.
Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown (watch closely).
In a small bowl, mix together melted butter and garlic powder.
Brush over biscuits when still warm and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 biscuits.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 baking dish; set aside.
Put 2 tablespoons margarine in a large skillet.
Put onions (not green onions), celery, carrots and peppers in food processor; coarsely chop.
Add to skillet.
Saute until chopped vegetables are tender.
Combine potatoes, green onions, sour cream, soup, milk, cheeses, salt and pepper.
Stir in sauteed vegetables.
Spoon into baking dish.
Cover mixture with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle remaining margarine over crumbs.
Bake about 1 hour or until crumbs are lightly browned and mixture is bubbling. Serve immediately.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Cream sugar with eggs; add butter, milk, flour and baking powder.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Cover top with melted butter and mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle over melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, reserving 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Pour mixture in large baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheese spread (sandwich)
directions: Melt cheese and butter in double boiler. Beat eggs well. Stir into melted cheese and butter, stirring constantly, until eggs are well cooked and thick. Add pimentos.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pie filling with water and let stand 5 minutes.
Then mix with fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: oven baked crab dip
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; mix well.
Gently stir in crabmeat.
Spoon crabmeat mixture into a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or more, if needed. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve warm with crackers.
Yield:
about 2 3/4 cups.

title: southern style corn
directions: Remove silk from ears of corn.
With sharp, paring knife, cut kernels from corn.
Scrape cobs well to remove juice.
Melt butter in a large frypan.
Stir in corn and juices.
Add water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 15 minutes. To thicken, blend flour into milk, and add to corn.
Bring to a boil.
Continue cooking 5 more minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix cottage cheese with Jell-O.
Stir in fruit cocktail and cool whip.
Chill.

title: chicken ala marge
directions: Mix oil and wine.
Place chicken in roasting pan.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle oregano over chicken pieces. Thinly slice an onion and put on chicken.
Take 2 cans stewed tomatoes, crush them and pour over tomatoes and juice over chicken.
Top with mushrooms and seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Put chili sauce and jam in pan.
Simmer.
Cut hot dogs into 1-inch pieces and put in sauce.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Add all ingredients in large soup pot and simmer for at least one hour.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts!

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots; cut into 2-inch cylinders.
Bring all ingredients except parsley, to a boil over moderate heat.
Cover and simmer over low heat.
Shake skillet occasionally to roll carrots about. If liquid cooks away too fast, add more water.

title: budapest chops
directions: Beat the meat, dip in flour and fry quickly in hot fat on both sides.
Remove from pan and place in large clean pan.
Use the same fat to fry the chopped onion.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add salt and soda.
Fold in oats, then corn flakes.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown for 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Grate cheese; brown ground beef and drain.
Cook spaghetti and drain.

title: dieters' pie
directions: *Note:
If not dieting, use 2 teaspoons cornstarch instead of flour and 1/2 heaping cup of sugar instead of Sweet 'N Low.

title: hot spiced tea from tang
directions: *Or, use lemon flavored unsweetened or sugar sweetened instant tea.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute
onions in oleo; add soups, chili powder, chopped peppers and chicken.
Soften tortillas in hot shortening a few seconds, or
warm
in microwave for a few seconds.	Put 1 or 2 tablespoons of
mixture on a tortilla; add a bit of cheese and roll.
Put	seam
side down in a greased casserole dish.
Thin leftover chicken mixture with chicken broth and pour about 1/4 cup broth
over
enchiladas.
Top
with rest of grated cheese. Heat in microwave or oven until cheese melts.
Good with sour cream.

title: ski soup
directions: Cover and cook about 1 hour.

title: cinnamon ice cream
directions: Combine cinnamon stick pieces with the whole milk and whipping cream in a large saucepan.
Heat 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.
Take off heat and strain.
Pour into large saucepan.

Stir in sugar. Quickly whisk in egg yolks, one at a time. Cook over medium heat until mixture coats the back of a spoon. Strain into metal bowl. Set bowl in larger bowl if ice water until cool. Freeze according to directions with ice cream maker.
This is very rich and creamy. Place in freezer until ready to use.

title: pasta soup
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch slices and brown slightly.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add "Pasta Accents" and simmer 5 more minutes.
Parmesan cheese for garnish. May be doubled.

title: grace's sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake and mash potatoes.
Add first 5 ingredients and put in casserole dish and top with mixture of 1/3 c. oleo, flour, brown sugar and chopped nuts.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May need to bake an additional 5 to 15 minutes.

title: mrs. maggie's fruit cake
directions: Mix nuts, raisins, fruit, spice and flour.
In another bowl, mix eggs, margarine and molasses.
Combine well the first 2 mixes. Grease a round (8-inch) deep pan.
Line bottom and sides of pan with wax paper and let paper hang over edges of pan.
Spray with Pam spray.
Pour mix into pan.
Trim top of cake with cherries and pecan halves.
Completely cover top of cake pan with wax paper and tie down with string.
Place on rack in large canner.
Fill canner with hot water to reach 1/2 way up pan.
Start to boil and turn down.
Replace water to keep halfway in pan.
Cook 2 1/2 hours. Remove and place in oven at 300° until paper is dry.
Cool overnight.

title: sour cream-prune cake
directions: Pour boiling water over prunes and let stand 15 minutes. Drain and dice prunes.
Add 1 teaspoon lemon rind and set aside.

title: great salad dressing
directions: Combine in blender and serve.

title: ground beef and noodle casserole
directions: Combine meat and onion; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook in oil for 5 minutes or until slightly browned.
Drain fat.
Cook noodles in salted water until tender.
Place a layer of meat mixture in casserole dish.
Add a layer of noodles and top with Mexicorn.
Repeat process.
Pour diluted tomato soup over all. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue casserole
directions: Bake chicken; peel chicken from bone after cool.
Boil 2 packages of broccoli and cheese.
Cook rice.
Use a large casserole dish; place rice on the bottom.
Next, add broccoli and cheese for the second layer.
Place chicken on the broccoli and cheese for third layer.
Next, cover chicken with barbecue sauce. Bake at 375° until sauce is baked on chicken.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Use your hands and mix until creamy and smooth.
Divide into 4 parts.
Roll each part into a long thin roll.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together the first 6 ingredients in recipe. Add remaining 5 ingredients; mix well. Stir in nuts, coconut and chocolate chips. Either form into balls with your hands or drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil and freeze until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.
Garnish with additional strawberries, if desired.

title: tasty turkey pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix dressing, flour, bouillon and pepper in saucepan.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring frequently on low heat, until thickened.
Add turkey and vegetables.
Cook, stirring, until heated.
Spoon in 8-inch square baking dish. Unroll dough in 2 rectangles.
Press perforations together to seal.
Place rectangles, side by side, to form square.
Press edges together to form seam.
Cut dough in 1-inch strips.
Arrange in lattice design over turkey mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until golden.
Prep time:
20 minutes.
Cooking time:
20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: banana squares
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form, set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar, beat in egg yolks and mix well.
Add bananas. Combine flour and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites and nuts. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Melt margarine and cream cheese in saucepan.
Add tomato soup. Remove from heat.
Stir in chopped onion, celery and crabmeat. Add Knox gelatine.
Pour in greased mold.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: prize winning zucchini casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Set oven at 350°.
Combine all ingredients; put into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until browned.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 as side dish, 3 as a main dish.

title: quick cream cheese pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill 3 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water and drain.
Melt cheese with milk. Fold in broccoli.
Mix crumbs with melted butter.
Put in 1/2 broccoli, then add 1/2 of crumbs.
Add rest of broccoli and crumbs on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press half of mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom-bacon pate
directions: Cook mushrooms, onions and parsley in oleo for 5 minutes. Stir in lemon juice.
Beat together cream cheese, peanut butter, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce until fluffy.
Stir in mushroom mixture.
Chill.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped peanuts and crumbled bacon to coat.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in cold water. Add sugar and pineapple.
Cook 10 minutes. Cool.
Add cream cheese. Beat until smooth. Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour in long dish and chill.

title: zucchini beef bake
directions: Place ground beef and onions in fry pan.
Brown and drain. Add 3/4 tsp. salt, 1/4 tsp. thyme, and 1/4 tsp. pepper.
In a kettle melt 1/2 c. margarine and add the flour, 1 tsp.
salt and 1/2 tsp. pepper.
Add milk, all at once.
Stir; cooking until bubbly and thick.
Add cheese.
Cut zucchinis into 1/2 inch chunks.
Boil in salt water 2 minutes.
Place in bottom of 2 quart baking dish with meat mixture on top.
Cover meat mixture with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: meaty 3-bean bake
directions: Brown together ground chuck, bacon and onion.
Drain and set aside.
Mix together all other ingredients and add to meat mixture.
Bake at 350° about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Can also be cooked in crock-pot.

title: save your own sugar french fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate over hot water. Remove from heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk, vanilla, salt and, if desired, nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Turn into wax paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill; store in an airtight container.
Makes about 1 3/4 pounds.

title: tomato rice beef bake
directions: In 9 x 9-inch square baking dish, place tomatoes, rice and water.
Set aside.
In skillet, brown beef, onion and mushrooms. Salt to taste; drain fat.
Add to ingredients in baking dish. Place in oven for 15 minutes.
Cover top with cheese and bake until melted.

title: pineapple macadamia bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
In mixing bowl gradually beat 3/4 cup sugar into butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
Sift in about 1/2 flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Add pineapple (in its own juice) and nuts.
Stir in remaining flour mixture.
Spoon batter into pan.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together 3 times. Blend shortening and sugars together; add eggs. Mix well. Add vanilla and water. Add flour mixture. Mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 14 minutes.

title: spicy carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Mix oil and sugar.
Beat egg yolks, one at a time.
Continue to beat and add 5 tablespoons of hot water.
Add flour and spices.
Save 1/4 cup of carrots for top and stir in carrots and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: tempura batter no. 2
directions: To Make Batter: Beat together until all ingredients are just well moistened (a few lumps should remain). Keep batter cool with a few ice cubes in the batter. Dip vegetables in batter. Cook in deep hot fat (360° to 365°) until tender and browned. Drain thoroughly. Serve with condiments.

title: ham and swiss stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Tip:
Before beginning recipe, flatten chicken breasts to an even thickness.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each egg.
Mix in flour, vanilla and cinnamon.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool 30 minutes before removing.

title: poppy-seed cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and egg yolks.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed ingredients, alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla and poppy seed.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° in a lightly greased angel food cake pan for approximately 1 hour.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Combine Bisquick with oleo until well mixed.
Add milk and mix to make dough.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts and roll out as pie crust, only leave it thicker.
Brown sausage and spread over parts.
Begin from one corner and roll into a 2-inch roll.
Crimp ends and wrap with foil.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze for future use.

title: ice cream kolachies
directions: Cream butter and ice cream.
Blend in flour and mix into a workable dough.
Pinch off 1 teaspoon dough and form in ball about the diameter of a quarter.
Press a dent in dough with thumb and fill spot with fruit filling.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put pecans in bottom of pie shell.
Beat eggs, add butter, corn syrup and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour and mix all together.
Pour over nuts and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp butter
directions: In a large bowl drain shrimp juice and add gelatin.
Set aside.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk well.
Mix other ingredients and add to lemon mixture.
Put in pastry shell of your choice (plain or graham).
Chill several hours before serving.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Mix together and put in crock-pot on high for 1 hour.
Then cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.
Remove bay leaves and garlic. Thicken as desired.

title: pumpkin cake and icing
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Mix together next four ingredients, then add to dry ingredients.
Pour into greased flute pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour.
Add water; cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Blend in cheese and eggs.
Put broccoli in greased casserole.
Pour in sauce.
Cover with crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Pour 3 cups of hot water over jello and stir well.
Let cool. Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese until it is soft.
Add crushed pineapple and fold into jello after jello is cooled.
Mix well. Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: chicken with fettuccine
directions: Saut first 8 ingredients together in large pan until cooked. Add fresh tomatoes; let simmer for 10 minutes. Cook fettuccine per directions on back of box; drain. Mix well. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on individual servings.

title: caramel dip for apple
directions: Mix together with a food processor or blender.
Store in refrigerator if any leftover.

title: quick broccoli-cheese chicken
directions: Cook white rice according to package directions.
Spread rice on bottom of ungreased casserole dish.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice.
Pour can of broccoli-cheese soup over chicken and rice.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until chicken is done.

title: caramel bars
directions: Combine caramels and evaporated milk (1/3 cup) and cook over low heat until melted; set aside.
Mix together cake mix, butter, evaporated milk (1/3 cup) and nuts.
Stir until dough holds together.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in a 9 x 13 cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and caramel mixture. Sprinkle remainder of dough on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more at 350°.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together. Mix apples, raisins and pecans. Add to the first mixture. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix gently and freeze in foil muffin cups.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add beaten egg and milk and mix.
Bake one hour in slow oven or until done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix jello with cake mix.
Add water and Wesson oil and beat well.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating until all are added.
Mix in strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parslied salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and spices.
Add onions, tomatoes and parsley.
Marinate 1 hour or longer.
Pour on lettuce and toss lightly.
Top with croutons.

title: honey apple bran muffins with grand marnier
directions: Stir the Raisin Bran, orange juice, egg, oil and honey together until mixture is blended.
Stir in apple.
Add remaining ingredients all at once and stir until mixture is moistened and even.
Do not overmix.
Divide batter into 12 paper-lined muffin cups and bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Place squash half cut side down in a baking pan with 1/4 inch of water.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Turn over.
Mix all other ingredients and fill the squash with the apple mixture.
Bake 15 more minutes.

title: cracker salad
directions: Chop first 5 ingredients fine, then mix with cracker crumbs and salad dressing (do not use mayonnaise).
Chill overnight. Very good on any cracker.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
Add whole eggs and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add 1 cup flour and all dry ingredients.
Add sour milk, water and rest of flour alternately.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: cranberry orange ham glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; mix well.
Brush or spoon mixture over ham the last 30 minutes of baking time.
Glaze may also be served with the ham.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer casserole with lettuce and chopped celery.
Cook peas several minutes in microwave.
Layer peas, chopped red onion, chopped green pepper and chopped ham. Cover top with mayonnaise and seal the edges.
Sprinkle with sugar, grated cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Bacon can be cooked in microwave.
If fried, cool, drain and break into pieces. Toss salad before serving.
Place in a serving dish.

title: mocha truffles
directions: In microwave bowl, melt chocolate chips.
Add cream cheese, coffee and water.
Mix well.
Chill until firm enough to shape. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill 1 to 2 hours or until firm.
Melt chocolate coating in microwave.
Dip balls and place on waxed paper to harden.
Melt white chocolate and drizzle over truffles.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: mandarin orange congealed salad
directions: Thaw Cool Whip.
Place in a large, deep bowl.
Sprinkle the dry jello over the Cool Whip and mix well.
Add the cottage cheese and mix well.
Toss the orange slices into the mixture along with the slivered almonds.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and carrots; mix well. Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with white frosting.

title: nut goody bars
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Add peanut butter. Let cool slightly; add marshmallows and peanuts.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: blueberry-banana bread
directions: Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons flour; set aside.
Combine remaining flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg in a small bowl.
Cream margarine in a large bowl; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Gently fold in reserved blueberries.

title: egg, ham and cheese bagel(bacon or sausage also)
directions: Slice bagel in half and place in a buttered skillet face down (or butter the bagel slices and place in skillet).
If bagels are a nice golden brown, then flip over onto other side and cook until lightly browned (if so desired).
Take one or two eggs.
Mix eggs with salt, pepper and milk (optional).
Prepare eggs to your desire (scrambled, sunny side up, etc.).
Take your choice of meat and fry in skillet also.
Place cheese on eggs immediately after they're cooked.
This way the cheese can melt.
Mayonnaise is for spreading on the bagel.

title: olive corn bread
directions: Add hot
water
to
salt and honey in mixing bowl.
Let cool to about
Add
yeast and stir.
Cover and let rise in warm place until bubbly, 15 minutes.
Chop olives coarsely. Stir in olives, corn meal and flour to make a thick dough.

title: tuna souffl
directions: Take 6 slices of bread and butter both sides; line bottom flat baking dish.
Mix tuna, mushrooms, celery and onions and spread over the bread.
Cover with the remaining slices of bread.
Combine mayonnaise, milk and eggs and pour over the bread.
Refrigerate overnight; sauce will be absorbed.
Pour soup over the top and sprinkle with the grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Boil pineapple, juice and water 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O and dissolve.
Then add cream cheese and blend until dissolved.
Let cool.
Then add apples, nuts, celery and Cool Whip.
Cool in refrigerator until congealed.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, the baking powder and salt in ungreased square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with ice cream.
Spoon sauce from pan onto each serving.

title: kool-aid pies
directions: Mix all together Cool Whip, milk and Kool-Aid. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain well.
Saute onion in margarine.
Beat egg.
Mix squash, onion, egg, sugar, mayonnaise, crackers and 1/2 of cheese.
Put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top; dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: tropical pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add margarine, pineapple and coconut. Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and blend. Add milk, dates, nuts and flour with baking powder.
Bake in a greased and floured 8-inch square dish at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: easy crab imperial
directions: Cook ingredients until thick.
Add 1 pound crabmeat.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Brown in a 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat through over low heat until all blended and warm.
Serve warm with Melba crackers.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and marshmallows in a large microwave bowl.
When melted, gradually add cereal and mix thoroughly.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: furrs pecan pie
directions: Bake at 425° in unbaked pie shell for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salt water until tender. Drain well. Brown sausage and onions; drain off fat. Mix all ingredients together; pour in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain and set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients in a saucepan (you may need to add about 1 cup of water to this mixture)
Bring this to a boil.
