Combine hamburger meat and soup mixture in a large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about one hour.
This recipe may be stretched by adding more meat and/or potatoes.

title: beef with ravioli dumplings
directions: In plastic bag, combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Add beef cubes, a few at a time, shaking to coat.
In skillet, brown meat quickly in hot oil.
Add onion, garlic and oregano; cook until onion is tender but not brown.
Transfer to crock-pot.
Add 1 cup water.
Cook on low heat setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Turn crock-pot to high heat.
Rinse peas under hot water to separate; stir into beef mixture with ravioli and parsley.
Cover and cook until heated through, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rice stuffed flounder
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown onion and mushrooms in hot margarine.
Mix broth, half and half, cornstarch and dill; add to pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice; return to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in carrot and zucchini.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: chicken paradise
directions: Marinate boneless
chicken
breasts 48 hours.
Marinade can be turned
into sauce for chicken if needed or remove from marinade and broil or grill.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter and remove from pan.
Cut steak into strips approximately 2 1/2-inches long and 3/4-inch wide.
Melt additional 2 tablespoons butter in a pan.
Coat steak strips with flour and brown steak in butter.
Add salt, onions and soup.
Stir in 1/2 can of water.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until meat is tender, about 1 1/4 hours.
Add sour cream; heat. Serve over noodles.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Have strawberries partially defrosted.
(Be careful, don't let them thaw too much, only enough so you can kind of chop them apart.)
Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend only till all strawberries are chopped.
It will be very icy and slushy.
Serve in glasses with straws to sip.
This is a quick way to brighten up a supper on a warm summer day.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar with flour and cinnamon.
Add beaten eggs and sour cream last.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook in moderate oven.

title: pizelles
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar a little at a time until smooth.
Add melted butter and desired flavoring.
Slowly add flour and baking powder, sifted together.
Batter should be fairly thick.
Spray pizelle iron with Pam.
Spoon 1 teaspoon in center of design.
Takes about 1/2 minute.

title: barbecue sauce(just a pinch of this and a pinch of that.)
directions: This is a very good recipe, but you have to use your judgement as to the amount you want to use.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Blend margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternate with milk chocolate. Add vanilla.
Cook in tube pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°. Test for doneness.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Slice onions in 1/2 inch rounds.
Separate each ring, using the largest ones.
Soak 1 hour in bowl with enough milk to cover onion rings.
Mix rest of ingredients; fold in egg whites.
Dip onion rings in batter and fry.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and add oleo.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: williamsburg casserole
directions: Brown ground beef (drain).
Add cream of mushroom soup, carrots and green beans.
Mix together; place in 4-quart casserole.
Cover with a layer of mashed potatoes.
Add a few pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned.

title: cookies to make the blues go away (oatmeal raisin)(to mom with love)
directions: Mix raisins, walnuts and flour to coat; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugars, adding a little at a time.
Add one egg at a time; add vanilla.
Mix.
Sift all dry ingredients, except oats, in another bowl.
Add this to sugar and shortening.
Mix in nuts and raisins; add oats.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Put 1/2 dry cake mix in greased pan.
Put apples and juice on top.
Top with other half of mix; sprinkle a cup of sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: mama's german chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornstarch together, blending well.
Add eggs; mix well, then add melted oleo and chocolate, mixing only until blended and smooth.
Gradually add evaporated milk, mixing and keeping bowl scraped down well.
Stir in vanilla (more than 1 teaspoon if desired) and salt.
Sprinkle flaked coconut over bottom of two 10-inch unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top of coconut.
Turn chocolate mixture into shells and bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Add bananas, one at a time; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Grease loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°, then lower heat to 350° and bake another 35 to 45 minutes.

title: rice mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in airtight container.
Remove cooking instructions from box and place in container also.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cut Velveeta into chunks and place in saucepan with milk. Heat on medium to melt cheese.
Stir constantly.
Brown sausage and ground beef and drain.
Mix meat and cheese.
Add tomatoes and green chiles (if desired).
Pour in crock-pot and turn on warm when ready to eat.
Serve with any brand of nacho chips.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Place 1/2 in pan or dish, about 9 x 13-inch.
Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Add milk, dry Dream Whip and sugar.
Beat with mixer until smooth.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Layer in 9 x 13 pan all vegetables. Crush crackers; add melted oleo to crackers and set aside.
Pour taco sauce over vegetables.
Put cracker mixture on top.
Add shredded cheese if desired.
Bake 1 hour.

title: carrot nut bread
directions: Beat sugar and salad oil; add eggs.
Then add sifted ingredients.
Add nuts and grated carrots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in crock pot which has been lightly greased.
Cut thin slices of cheese or sprinkle shredded cheese and put on top.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low.
Yields 12 servings.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not let rise.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° (until brown) in a greased muffin pan.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar together.
Stir in beaten egg and vanilla.
Shape into 1 inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with dinner fork to flatten slightly.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Shorter baking time will yield softer cookies.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: banana layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Melt the butter.
Mix stuffing; set aside.
Mix the soup and broth in another bowl; set aside.
Layer in buttered casserole dish the stuffing, chicken, soup mixture; again stuffing, chicken, soup mixture.
Save some stuffing to sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl and mix well. Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: cheese appetizer cookies
directions: Lightly spoon flour into a measuring cup; level off.
In a medium bowl, combine cheese, margarine, flour, salt and red pepper; mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill dough for 1 hour.

title: 7-up meatballs
directions: Mix together beef, water, bread crumbs, salt, soup mix and egg.
Roll into meatballs and brown.
Bring 7-Up and catsup to a boil.
Drop browned meatballs into 7-Up-catsup mixture.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Delicious and great for potlucks and picnics.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and egg, then chop egg, potatoes, celery, radishes, peppers and onion (finely chopped).
Add to the chopped mixture, the remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Pour into pastry pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: aunt ann's italian meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Form mixture into balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven until brown (15 to 20 minutes).
Put meatballs into favorite spaghetti sauce and simmer together until fully cooked.
Always use Italian bread crumbs!

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in large frypan.
Add garlic and peppers and brown. Add clam sauce and simmer for 1 hour.
Cook linguine as per instructions on box.
Cook broccoli.
Combine frypan mix with linguine and drained broccoli in large casserole.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and grated Italian Romano cheese.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini martini
directions: Wash, then trim the ends from the zucchini.
Then slice in even 1/4-inch rounds.
Set aside.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and eggs well (do not beat).
Add corn; stir in thoroughly.
Add milk.
Dot butter on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour (center firm and golden brown).

title: picnic barbecue beans
directions: Chop onion and celery.
Saute in a large pan.
When onion is translucent, add beans.
Season with brown sugar or molasses, ketchup, dash of Worcestershire sauce, dash of Tabasco sauce and salt and pepper.
Cook slowly.
Serve hot.

title: hot rolls
directions: Measure water into mixing bowl, sprinkle yeast over water and stir until dissolved. Add sugar, margarine, egg, salt and half the flour; beat until smooth. Mix in remaining flour until dough is easy to handle. Place dough in greased bowl, grease top of dough and cover with foil. Refrigerate at least 2 hours. When dough rises, punch it down. When fresh rolls are desired, cut off amount needed and return rest to refrigerator. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Dough may be kept 3 to 4 days.

title: ellen's boursin
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Empty scalloped potato mix, including seasoning, into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Heat tomatoes, water and oregano to boiling.
Stir into potatoes.
Arrange pepperoni on top and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Over low heat, cook water, milk, rice and salt.
Cook until rice is soft.
Then add sugar.
Then add the pudding.
Then pour in dishes and serve.
May be served warm or chilled.
If desired, sprinkle cinnamon.

title: top of stove rice pudding
directions: Simmer 45 minutes or until liquid is evaporated.
Keep stirring.
Try not to let it stick.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; serve.
Great for family reunions.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Fritos.
Add Fritos just before serving or they will become soggy.

title: lush
directions: Mix margarine, flour and chopped nuts and press into 13 x 9-inch
pan.
Bake	15 minutes at 375°.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese
and
Cool
Whip
and spread on crust while warm. Mix instant
pudding
mix
and milk and spread on cream cheese mixture.
Add rest of Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Add all ingredients to browned, drained hamburg.
Bring to a boil and cover, simmer for 20 minutes.
Add the macaroni, green beans and cabbage, cooking until everything is tender.

title: light as a feather doughnuts
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large, warm mixing bowl. Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, egg and half of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place
broccoli
in
bottom of Pyrex dish.
Put chicken breasts, bite-size,
on top of broccoli.
Pour soup and mayonnaise mixture over this.	Sprinkle cheese on top and onions on top of cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: tater-dipped vegetables
directions: In a small bowl, combine potato flakes, Parmesan cheese, celery salt, garlic powder and butter.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Dip vegetables, one at a time, into egg, then into potato mixture, coating well.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with dressing or dip.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: saucy steak skillet
directions: Coat steak with flour, pound into beef, brown beef in oil in 10-inch skillet.
Remove beef.
Cook and stir onion in oil until tender, add enough water to reserve potato liquid to measure 1 cup. Dissolve beef broth in 1/4 cup water.
Add all ingredients to skillet, heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, approximately 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepperoni pizza hot dish
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add potatoes, then browned and drained hamburger.
Heat Cheddar cheese soup with milk.
Pour over potatoes and hamburger.
Mix tomato soup, oregano and onion.
Pour over Cheddar cheese soup.
Put sliced pepperoni over it.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 1 hour or until the potatoes are done.
Take out and add Mozzarella cheese. Heat until melted.
Yummy!

title: welsh currant cookies
directions: Heat butter and molasses together until the butter has melted. Blend in the brown sugar.
Mix in the flour and ginger thoroughly.
While mixture is still hot, roll out dough, a small amount at a time, on a lightly floured board.
It should be very thin.
Cut with cookie cutters, hearts, diamonds, etc.
Put on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven, 325°, for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
When rolled thin makes about 12 dozen.

title: pie a la italiano(easter pie)
directions: Unroll crescent rolls; separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place 5 triangles into pie pan, pressing together to form crust. Reserve 3 triangles for top crust.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl; pour into crust.
Roll out each triangle so longest side is 8 inches long.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips. Crisscross strips over filling to form a lattice top.
Flute edge. Bake for 60 or 70 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.
Do not overbake.

title: thick vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef until crisp in a heavy deep kettle.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer gently about 45 minutes over low heat.

title: goof balls
directions: Melt oleo and pour over chopped nuts.
Add 2 boxes sifted powdered sugar, condensed milk, coconut and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Roll into small balls and put in refrigerator 15 minutes.
Melt 2 packages of chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and cool.

title: buckeye's (peanut butter balls)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients (best done with your hands) until stiff.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator until set, about 30 minutes.
In a double boiler with water at simmer, melt chocolate and shortening.
Remove from heat.
Using toothpick dip peanut butter balls to cover 3/4 of ball.
Smooth over toothpick holes and chill.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, green pepper, onion and carrot in bowl.
Bring to a boil the oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard, celery seed and salt. Pour hot liquid over vegetables. Do not stir.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, shortening and potatoes.
Blend all dry ingredients and beat in until smooth.
Turn to lightly cover with flour on a flour covered cloth.
Roll gently 1/3-inch thick.
Cut into circles with doughnut cutter after chilling for 2 to 3 hours.

title: beef logs
directions: Mix all together for 5 minutes.
The next 2 days, knead for 5 minutes.
The fourth day, roll into logs.
Put on a broiler pan. Bake 8 hours at 180°, turning 1/4 turn every 2 hours.
When done, roll on a paper towel to absorb grease.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Use an 11 1/2 x 8-inch pan.
Place butter in pan and melt in oven.
Sprinkle and press crushed graham crackers onto melted butter.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Sprinkle chocolate chips. Sprinkle butterscotch chips.
Drizzle Eagle Brand condensed milk. Sprinkle chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan, then cut into squares.

title: white mountain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and milk alternately a little at a time.
Save 1 cup flour to mix with baking powder. Beat the egg whites to a stiff froth.
Combine the leftover flour and baking powder and add it to mixture.
Add egg froth, then the flavoring.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except celery.
Chill for 2 hours.
Just before serving, add celery.
Makes six servings.
Each serving provides 1/2 vegetable exchange, 2 fat exchanges, 1 protein exchange and 9 optional calories.

title: sweet-sour broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, peanuts, raisins and onions.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; pour over vegetables and toss to coat.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: "mama's" cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, eggs and milk well. Add a little sugar. Pour into a greased heated iron skillet. Bake in a 450° oven for about 20 minutes or until golden.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Separate rolls and fill with 2 or 3 chicken strips; roll up tightly.
Place in a well greased baking dish.
Pour soup over rolls evenly.
Sprinkle with shredded cheddar.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Bake in a
loaf or patties.
Serve with egg gravy.

title: spinach everyone likes
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Break salmon into fine pieces and add beaten egg, lemon juice, onion, salt and 1 tablespoon of cracker crumbs.
Form into cakes (4-inches wide by 1/2-inch thick).
Roll in remainder of crumbs and fry until golden brown.
If using deep fat fryer, start on high and switch to medium high (375°) for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole(cholesterol free)
directions: Cook dumplings.
Place the next 4 ingredients in baking dish. Add dumplings, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat at 350° until bubbly and slightly brown.
If a little dry, add a little more water.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and set aside.
Put potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over potatoes.
Lay pork chops on top and layer onions.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Last 15 minutes, uncover and spread cheese and finish baking.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Put starter in the refrigerator 3 to 5 days (keep in jar covered with foil).
Take out and feed with sugar, potatoes and warm water.
Mix well and add to starter.
Let stand out of refrigerator all day, 8 to 12 hours.
Mixture will be very bubbly. Stir; take out one cup to make bread and return starter to refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator 3 to 5 days and feed again. If you are not making bread after feeding starter, throw away one cup.
This is to avoid deflating your starter.

title: salmon and cheese ball
directions: Remove	skin
and
bones from salmon.
Place in a bowl. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into a ball and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: brazilian shrimp stroganoff
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in butter and olive oil.
Add the shrimp; cook until pink, then add the tomatoes, ketchup, mustard, parsley, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Add the sour cream.
Ready to serve.
Serves 8 people.
Serve with rice, salad or vegetables.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt
butter
and
pour
in
ovenware dish.
Mix flour, sugar and
milk
together and pour on top of butter.
Pour can of peaches
on
top.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for about one hour or until top is golden brown and springs back.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Add sugar. Beat until mixture is smooth. Add egg yolks. Beat well.

title: four layer ground beef casserole
directions: First Layer:
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and rinse.
Add soup, sour cream, cream cheese and milk, plus 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt.
Spread in shallow casserole.

title: sausage with peppers and onions in sauce
directions: Cut sausage into pieces about 2 to 3 inches long.
Brown sausage.
Fry peppers and onions together.
Combine sausage, peppers and onions in a casserole.
Add enough sauce to just cover the contents.
Cover.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Good served on large buns.

title: "farm punch"
directions: Boil
sugar
and water for 10 minutes.	Cool.
Mix with strong tea
(I
make
double
strength).	Cool
syrup and tea mixture. Add
lemon	juice, lime juice, white grape juice and orange juice and continue to chill.

title: white icing
directions: Combine milk and flour well.
Let thicken under low fire in pot. Let come to a near boil.
Do not burn!
Let cool down.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer chicken and broccoli.
Pour mixed soup, mayonnaise, cheese and curry powder over.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake until bubbly at about 350°.

title: herbal oils
directions: You will need wide mouth jars.

title: venison gumbo
directions: Brown
venison; set aside.
Saute in butter the onions, celery, green onions and bell pepper until onions are clear in color.
Set aside.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine shortening and boiling water.
Stir until shortening is melted.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat in cold water in another bowl.
Soften yeast in warm water in another bowl.
Combine 3 mixtures.
Add flour.
Dough will
be too soft to knead.
Mix with a heavy spoon until flour is mixed in completely.
Cover and chill overnight.
Remove dough from refrigerator; punch down. Pinch off amount needed to form each roll.
Shape and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Shape remaining dough into neat ball and keep in refrigerator (well covered).
Fresh rolls every day!

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased pan at 350°.
May be baked in loaf pan or muffin pan.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt gradually.
Add milk. Microwave on High 7 minutes (stir every 3 minutes).
Take 1 egg (beaten well); add small amount of hot pudding into egg.
Add all to milk mixture; stir well.
Microwave on Medium-high for 3 minutes (stir after first minute).
Add the butter and vanilla. Layer as usual with bananas and wafers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Cream sugar, eggs, butter and shortening.
Add flour, soda and milk.
Mix well.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add egg whites and mix.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: toasty nut granola
directions: Heat
oats
in	low
sided
pan at 350° for 10 minutes. Combine
oats,
brown
sugar, wheat germ, coconut, sesame seed and nuts.
Add oil, honey and vanilla.	Mix until dry ingredients
are well coated.
Divide oat mixture into 2 equal parts. Bake
half the oat mixture in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan
in preheated
oven
for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring often to brown evenly.
Cool.
Stir until crumbly.
Repeat for remaining half
of
oat
mixture.
Store
covered
tightly in refrigerator.

title: black bean soup
directions: In small bowl, cover dried tomatoes with boiling water and set aside.
Saute onions, garlic and cayenne in oil for 5 minutes.
Add cumin, 1/3 cup water and chopped, canned tomatoes.
Add to pan (with juice).
Cover and bring to boil.
Lower heat, simmer uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add beans and water, simmer and stir occasionally.
Drain and chop softened sun-dried tomatoes.
Add to soup and cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in the cilantro and remove from heat.
Puree 1/2 of the soup in blender.
Return to pan.
If soup is too thick, add water or tomato juice.
Reheat slowly.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until light and creamy.
Add other ingredients and beat until light.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: nutty-crunch-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add sugars and mix well.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to first mixture, beating well until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Makes about 9 dozen.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Blend eggs and sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add topping to hot cake.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruits, reserving all juices except from apples.
(A very small amount of the apple juice may be used for color.) Arrange fruit in casserole dish.
Combine sugar, butter, flour, sherry and juices.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Pour over fruit and let stand several hours in refrigerator.
Let warm up to room temperature before baking in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Good with beef, pork or poultry.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburg; drain grease.
Add 3/4 cup water and taco mix. Put in large salad bowl.
Add the lettuce, tomatoes, onion, cucumber, green pepper, cheese and Catalina dressing.
Just before serving, add the crushed Doritos.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice enough medium sized cucumbers to fill a gallon jar. Cover with 1/2 cup pickling salt or canning salt and 2 quarts boiling hot water.
Let this stand for 24 hours.
Drain and cover with 2 teaspoons alum and 2 quarts boiling hot water.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: vegetarian chili with rice
directions: In a heavy Dutch oven (6-quart), heat vegetable oil over moderately low heat for 1 minute; add the onion, carrot, garlic and green pepper.
Cook, covered, 10 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Add lentils, chili powder, cumin, bay leaf, cayenne pepper and tomatoes, along with a small amount of water if the mixture appears thick.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add chickpeas, black and pinto beans.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes or until lentils are tender.
Before the chili is done, cook the rice following package directions, omitting the salt.
Ladle chili over rice.
Serves 4.

title: nana's gingerbread
directions: Combine butter, sugar and molasses in mixing bowl.
Stir together with wooden spoon.
Add soda to hot water and stir.
Add to main bowl.
Mix in flour, ginger and cinnamon.
Add beaten eggs last.
Stir mixture and pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Test with a toothpick.

title: chicken fandango(for crockpot)
directions: Cut up chicken and brush with butter. Place in crockpot. Sprinkle Italian dressing over chicken. Add onion. Cook on low 6-8 hours. Add rest of ingredients. Heat through. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat well all ingredients, except raisins and nuts.
After batter has been beaten well, add raisins and nuts.
Beat well. Pour into a well-greased loaf pan or any pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: spinach cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then melt oleo in large baking dish.
Pour in mixture and bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour, or until done.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and bananas.
Sift dry ingredients and add oatmeal.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
May add raisins and nuts, if desired.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool spaghetti.
Mix together tomatoes, cucumber, Bermuda onion, black olives, French's spaghetti mix and Italian dressing.
Pour over spaghetti.
Chill.
Prepare at least 24 hours ahead of time so flavors have time to blend.

title: clam casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in stuffing mix.
Add clams and juice, onions, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Put into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with fresh bread crumbs.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Add eggs, onion and parsley; toss.
Whisk oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni.
Do not toss.
Cover and marinate at room temperature for 1 hour.
Stir in mayonnaise; toss gently.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in double boiler.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and coconut.
Mix well. Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax, then dip balls and place on waxed paper.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Use a covered roasting pan or a Reynolds baking bag which has 1 tablespoon flour in it.
Preheat oven to 325°.
If using the bag, place this in a 2-inch deep pan.
Remove membrane from the outside of leg of lamb.
Trim at least 3/4 fat.
Combine garlic, herbs and salt and pepper.
Rub this all over the lamb.
Place lamb in bag and follow the directions on package.
Bake until meat thermometer reads 150°.
Bake for 2 hours then let it stay in bag for 15 minutes.
Slice and serve with mint jelly.

title: coconut cake
directions: Sift into mixing bowl flour and sugar.
Add shortening and half of milk.
Blend two minutes.
Add remaining milk, eggs and vanilla and beat two minutes.
Pour into two 8-inch prepared pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes in preheated oven at about 350°.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Melt butter with garlic and simmer a few minutes. Mix bread crumbs and cheese.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the crackers and margarine.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix crackers and margarine; sprinkle on top and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole; place spinach in casserole. Coarsely flake tuna over spinach.
Drain mushrooms in 1 cup measure.
Add lemon juice and water to make 1 cup.
In saucepan over low heat, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour, onion, salt and season.
Stir in mushroom liquid and cook until thick.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in covered casserole.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place the mixture in a loaf pan or shape into a loaf and place in a baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm when pressed in the center.

title: pineapple delight(this is a good pineapple dessert.)
directions: Place bread cubes and pineapple in a baking dish.
Mix and cook, in a saucepan, the pineapple juice, butter, flour and sugar, until thick.
Pour over bread and pineapple.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine water, mushroom soup, bouillon cubes and rice in a casserole or cake pan.
Place pieces of chicken in "slop." Sprinkle package of dry onion soup mix over the top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple raisin drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg and beat until light.
Add fruits and nuts.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate, oatmeal and peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over oatmeal.
Stir and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper; let cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl except tortillas and cheese. Cut tortillas in fourths and grate cheese.
In greased casserole, put 1/2 cut tortillas.
Pour 1/2 mixture over them and 1/2 of the cheese.
Continue with second layer.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly and hot, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Take 3/4 package of Oreos and spread in the bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Slice ice cream. Lay on top of Oreos. Slightly warm sauce and pour over ice cream. Spread whipped topping over sauce. Top with remaining crushed Oreos. Freeze 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 10 inch skillet.
Spread brown sugar evenly in pan and arrange pineapple slices on sugar.
Put cherries in centers of slices and fill in spaces with pecan halves.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg whites.
Pour batter over pineapple. Bake at 375 degrees for 30-35 minutes.
Turn upside down on cake plate. 1 10 inch cake.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler with milk.
Add pecans and stir.
Drop in small patties on buttered cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate and paraffin.
Cover patties.
Cool.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over very low heat; cool.
Sift flour with sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir butter in mixing bowl to soften.
Add flour mixture, 3/4 cup of the buttermilk and the vanilla.
Mix to dampen flour; beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add melted chocolate, eggs and remaining buttermilk; beat 1 minute longer.
Pour batter into three 8-inch pans, lined on bottoms with paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until cake tester inserted into centers come out clean.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on racks.
Spread Filling on layers and stack.

title: orange bars
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a large greased pan (10 x 15-inch).
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice while still warm with grated rind of orange, orange juice and powdered sugar.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: turkey and potato pie
directions: Put sliced vegetables on bottom of casserole dish.
Put hamburger over other ingredients (like a lid).
Punch several holes with your finger into meat.
Pour can of tomato sauce and can of water over top of meat.
Cover and bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, 1 cup of sugar, baking powder, milk and oil. Pour into a greased shallow 3-quart baking dish.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Press 1 package rolls into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread over rolls in pan.
Top with remaining package crescent rolls, pressed together and flattened to fit.

title: messy tacos
directions: Brown hamburger and cook beans about 30 minutes on high.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on high for 30 minutes. Then turn down on low and cook 2 or 3 hours.

title: rainbow jello dessert
directions: Mix 1 packet of jello; follow directions on box, but instead of cold water, mix in 9 tablespoons of vanilla ice cream.
Let set, then continue with other flavors the same way.
When all flavors are layered and set, take out of pan,
place on a plate and cover with whipped cream.
Slice and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish ingredients in order given.
Mix butter with Ritz crackers for the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend Cool Whip and cream cheese together until smooth. Add crushed pineapple and sugar and mix well. Pour into graham cracker pie shell and refrigerate until ready to serve. Refrigerate any unused portions.

title: pizza burger
directions: Fry together the chuck, oregano, onion and green pepper.
Add the cheese, spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Heat oven to 500°. Put on open-faced bun.
Cover with grated Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: In skillet, brown chuck, onion and garlic until chuck
is crumbly; drain excess fat.
Cool.
Stir in cheese, crumbs, parsley and egg.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook shells in boiling, salted water until almost tender, about 15 minutes. Drain.
Use meat mixture to stuff shells.
Spoon 1/4 of sauce over bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place shells on top of sauce, side by side, in a single layer.
Mix wine with remaining sauce and pour over shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Serve sprinkled with additional grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine the ingredients in a large bowl.
Then pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or longer.
If desired, top with extra cheese halfway through baking time.

title: tostados
directions: Place beans on shells, add meat, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and top with picante sauce.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat well until fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Add extracts.
Pour into well greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Crush pretzel sticks.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup butter or oleo.
Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 7 minutes; cool.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix Crisco and other ingredients together.
Add cereal and milk.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill and serve cold.
Not good for sandwiches.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix well in the order given and refrigerate overnight.

title: minute rice(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine water, butter and salt. Microwave for 5 minutes at High (100% power) until it comes to a boil.
Add rice and stir well.
Microwave for 1 minute, covered, at High.
Let stand for 5 minutes, covered.
Fluff with a fork before serving.

title: hot crabmeat spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Turn into buttered ramekin.
Heat in 300° oven
for 15 minutes until hot and slightly puffy.
Serve at once with crackers.

title: pineapple pan stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In medium bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended. Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Turn into pie pan. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour until top is brown and crusty.

title: chocolate chip cake(one of my favorites.)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar by hand, then add flour and mix with a fork until it becomes crumbly.
Keep 1/2 cup aside for topping.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Put baking soda into sour cream and then into mix.
Add vanilla.

title: easy donuts
directions: Cut hole in middle of biscuit; drop in hot oil and roll in sugar coating.

title: strawberries through a straw
directions: In a large blender container combine frozen strawberries, pineapple juice and honey if desired.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Makes 4 (6 ounce) servings.

title: apple pudding
directions: Peel and slice baking apples.
Layer in the bottom of a square baking dish.
Pour hot water over the apples.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, cinnamon and 3 tablespoons flour.
Sprinkle over apples. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, egg, milk, 2 tablespoons melted butter, 1 1/4 cups flour and baking powder.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are done and top is browned (30 to 45 minutes).
Serve warm, topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy saucepan. Cook over high heat until mixture reaches 210° on candy thermometer. Let cool for 20 minutes; skim surface if necessary. Drizzle over cake. Sauce may be cooled and reheated in warm water.

title: low-fat potato casserole
directions: Layer thin sliced potatoes, then onion.
Sprinkle with pepper and rosemary, then shredded Parmesan cheese.
Use medium size baking dish.
Pour chicken broth over layers (use enough broth to cover potatoes).
Bake at approximately 350° for 45 minutes, covered, then approximately 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: grandma janie's senegalese jujus
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan.
Fry onions until they are slightly browned.
Add meat, salt and gharam masala and fry.
Cook until well done, breaking meat into small pieces.
Drain and cool.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Saute the chopped green onions in margarine.
At the same time, prepare Minute rice according to package directions and set aside.
After onions are sauteed, add eggs and salt.
Scramble until eggs are cooked.
Add chicken, peas and Minute rice.
Season with soy sauce to your taste.

title: mackerel pattie
directions: Mix well together and fry.

title: sister lealer cushen's tea cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding flour as needed.
Roll out cookie dough and cut out.
Bake at 350° on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mom's potato biscuits
directions: Mix the potatoes, sugar, milk, egg and yeast cake together. When it has stiffened, add the shortening and salt.
(Add flour, if needed, to stiffen; not too stiff.) Let set in warm place until double in amount.
Work it down and make into biscuits.
Put in pan and let raise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: butter cream icing
directions: Mix in large bowl. Beat until all lumps are out. Add 1/2 cup butter. Continue beating until icing is fairly light and fluffy.

title: white beans, ham and sausage
directions: Rinse beans; cover with lots of water.
Bring to boil; cook 3 minutes.
Turn fire out; let sit 2 hours.
Drain; rinse twice. Add water and rest of ingredients except sausage.
While beans are cooking, saute sausage.
Drain grease and add to beans.
When beans are done, use hand potato masher and mash beans about 12 times.
All beans will not be mashed.
This will thicken beans. We eat this with rice.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix first 5
ingredients.
Put waxed paper in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Spread nuts on top.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cool crust.
Mix jello and water.
Add pineapple and strawberries.
Layer on cream cheese mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: black-eyed peas with bacon
directions: Place peas, bacon and enough water to cover in a large pot; bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Do not drain.

title: cheese cake danish
directions: Place one can of rolls in bottom of pan.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Spread over rolls.
Place remaining can of rolls on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hoot gibson's italian meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Take garlic cloves and crush into salt until it turns to paste.
Combine all ingredients, except beef (should be a mixture like loose oatmeal).
Add in meat and mix with hands until well combined.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls. Place on baking sheet with no rack.
Bake for about 20 minutes. Makes about 120 meatballs.

title: blue ribbon-pumpkin drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco together.
Add egg, pumpkin, flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: peach pickles
directions: Tie ginger, cinnamon, cloves and allspice in cheesecloth bag. Add to vinegar 2 cups sugar and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil. Add peaches, a few at a time, until all peaches have been heated. Remove peaches. Pour boiling syrup over peaches. Cover and let stand 3 to 4 hours. Remove from syrup. Add 2 cups sugar to syrup; heat to boiling. Pour over peaches. Cover and let stand 12 to 18 hours in a cool place. Pack peaches into hot Ball jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Add remaining 1 to 2 cups sugar to syrup. Bring to boiling. Pour over peaches, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps. Process pints and quarts 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: grustoli
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
In separate bowl, combine beaten eggs, vanilla and lemon extract.
Melt butter in milk.
Add to eggs and extracts.
Then add sugar and flour combination.
Roll out like pie crust.
Flour area.
Roll out dough; cut into diamonds.
Fry in large frypan 1/2 full of shortening until light brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: white chocolate nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and milk in large bowl until well blended.
Add brown and white sugars gradually.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in white chocolate and nuts.
Drop level tablespoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool one minute and remove.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix ingredients together; store in a dry jar.
To make a batch, take 6 tablespoons of mix and 3/4 cup boiling water. Next, add a cup of cold water.
Put in popsicle molds.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Shave broccoli flowerets with a knife or chop very finely. Cook broccoli in chicken broth until tender. Add butter and half and half. Thicken with about 3 tablespoons cornstarch in a little water. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: corrie's ice cream cake
directions: Tear angel food cake into large, bite size pieces.
Scoop sherbet and vanilla ice cream into an angel food cake pan alternately with the cake pieces.
Pack ice cream and cake mixture down as you go.
(You will use all the cake but not all the ice cream.)
Freeze.
Cake will pop out of the pan as you turn cake upside down to unmold.
Ice with Cool Whip; keep in the freezer until time to serve.

title: impossible zucchini tomato pie
directions: Put into greased pie plate the zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese.
Mix the Bisquick, milk, eggs, salt and Mrs. Dash; beat until smooth.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, or until knife comes out clean.

title: garden salad mixture "no cooking"
directions: Clean peppers and remove stems and seeds.
Clean onion and leave about 2 1/2 inches of green tops.
Peel and dice cucumber. Peel (optional) and dice tomatoes.
Combine ingredients, salt and black pepper to taste and lightly coat mixture with Italian dressing.
Let stand covered about 1 hour prior to serving.

title: pizza bread
directions: Roll dough flat.
Mix eggs, oregano and garlic powder together.
Spread 3/4 of egg mixture over dough.
Cover with pepperoni and cheese.
Roll up and pinch edges together so it doesn't leak out.
Baste top with remaining egg mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: trout mash
directions: Boil cabbage just to soften; cut onions, peppers, mushrooms and potatoes.
Cut trout by slicing off of bone.
Combine all ingredients into tinfoil.
Add butter on top and any seasonings. Fold up tinfoil package and place on broiler or barbecue.
Cook for 1/2 hour or until vegetables are done.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: christmas lizzies
directions: Line cookie sheet with freezer paper. Do not grease. Sift all dry ingredients together. Cream sugar and butter. Add dry ingredients alternately with juice to butter and sugar mixture. Add fruit and nuts which have been lightly floured. Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 275° until brown (about 25 minutes).

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening.
Cool.
Sift together flour with powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light; add sugar, then chocolate mixture.
Blend.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: turkey, dressing and giblet gravy(from the files of dessie bell hayes)
directions: Cook one pan of cornbread and the same amount of biscuits or light bread.
Crumble and mix in big bowl.
Add onion and sprinkle with celery seed, sage and black pepper.
Add the broth off the turkey (or hen).
Save 2 cups broth for gravy.
Add milk and eggs to dressing mixture.
If need more liquid, add enough water to make a thin batter.
Put back in roaster with turkey (or hen) and bake slow until dressing is cooked through.

title: fred's artichoke dip
directions: Process all ingredients in a food processor until smooth. Microwave for 7 minutes in a microwave safe dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 8.

title: devil's ham and eggs
directions: Split and separate yellow and white of eggs.
All measurements are approximate due to taste preference.
With mixer, mix all other ingredients until smooth.
With teaspoon fill eggs and sprinkle on paprika.
Refrigerate and serve.
Makes 48 egg halves.

title: swedish casserole
directions: Add water to soup and rice.
Mix all thoroughly.
Prepare ahead of time either pork chops or chicken breasts by baking until almost done, then add to rice and soup.
Mix well.
Top with butter and potato chips or bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Check to see if good and hot, if not bake additional 15 minutes.

title: old fashion sauce(cake topping)
directions: Mix together. Boil to soft-ball stage.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together well; roll into small balls.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: artichoke dip 1
directions: Saute mushrooms and garlic in margarine.
Let cool.
In large bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Fold mushrooms and garlic. Spread on 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and Parmesan over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with nacho chips.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix first 6 items with 1/4 cup condensed soup and form into about 15 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Brown meat balls and garlic in vegetable oil or bacon in cook and serve skillet, then blend in remaining soup and 1 cup water.
Cover and simmer on low for about 40 minutes, until rice is tender.

title: frozen fruit salad lo-cal and fat free!
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Gently fold in fruit.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Cut in squares and serve. Serves 12 to 15.

title: pineapple red hot salad
directions: Cut pineapple into bite size pieces. Mix pineapple & juice with red hots and marshmallows. Chill overnight. Just before serving, stir in Cool Whip

title: bing cherry jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package using juice from 1 can of Bing cherries as part of the cold liquid.
Stuff each Bing cherry with a small piece of either walnut or pecan nut.
Add stuffed cherries to Jell-O mixture and chill until set.

title: broccoli ring
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add milk, cream, broccoli, onion, salt, pepper, paprika and nutmeg.
Mix.
Bake in greased 1-quart ring mold.
(Set in pan water.)
Bake in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: minestrone
directions: Saute onion and garlic in saucepan with butter.
Add parsley. Mix tomato paste with boiling water (about 2 cups) and add to saucepan.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add vegetables and remaining water. Cook and cover for 30 to 40 minutes.
Season with salt, pepper and oregano.
Add macaroni and cook for 20 minutes.
Top off with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain first 3 ingredients. Add all remaining ingredients; bring to boil. Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook beef with onion until meat is brown and onion is tender, drain.
Stir in beans, soup, 1/4 cup water, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Drop stiff potatoes by mounds on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cook brownie mix as directed.
Mix your chocolate pudding as directed; let set.
Layer cooled brownies with Cool Whip and chocolate pudding.
Top with blended Heath bars.

title: five layer casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat. Add onion; cook until transparent. Place ground beef and onion in greased casserole dish. Put vegetables on top of meat. Take both cans of soup and put into pan. Put enough water into bottom of cans to clean out cans and add. Combine soup and heat until hot. Pour over ingredients in casserole. Spread Tater Tots over top. Salt and pepper "small amount". Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair squares
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch shallow pan with graham crackers.
Beat pudding mix with milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread pudding mixture over crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Set aside.
Melt the chocolate and margarine together over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Add powdered sugar, beaten egg, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over top layer of crackers.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
To serve, cut in squares.

title: western beans
directions: Fry beans in a heavy 3-quart saucepan. Add onion. Cook until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes or until lentils are tender. Stir occasionally. Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and garlic juice and onion together 10 minutes on low.
Add tomatoes, sauce and Sauer's sauce mix.
Cook on low for 20 minutes.
Boil lasagne and layer sauce, lasagne, cheeses and repeat.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: frog's stew
directions: Cook and stir cattails in oil over medium heat until golden. Stir in 1 cup water, bouillon, salt, water skeeters, bay leaf and elodea.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, until lily roots are just tender and flavors are blended (15 minutes or so).
Serves 8 to 10 for 4 to 5 days.

title: chicken parisian
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour, paprika and pepper. Add chicken to coat. In skillet, brown chicken in margarine. Remove from pan. In same skillet, add remaining ingredients; simmer 3 minutes. Add chicken. Simmer covered 25 minutes or until tender. Serve with rice and salad.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in a 2-quart pan.
Mix and cook over LOW heat until creamy.
Good with shrimp, chicken, breadsticks or noodles.

title: "forget me" cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add sugar slowly.
Add salt and cream of tartar while beating.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by the teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Place in a 350° preheated oven and turn oven off immediately.
Leave overnight without opening oven.

title: glazed sausage bites
directions: In mixer bowl, combine egg, sausage, crackers, milk and sage. Beat at high speed on electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls (wet hands to shape easily).
In skillet, brown meat on all sides, shaking pan occasionally to keep balls round.
Pour off excess fat.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Boil raisins 20 minutes in 3 cups water.
Save 1 cup of water.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Line unpricked pie crust with 2 layers of heavy-duty foil. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 5 to 7 minutes more.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream butter and add brown and white sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Add coconut, oatmeal and gumdrops.
Stir until well mixed.
Add vanilla last and mix well. Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: copper country quiche
directions: In food processor with steel blade or in large mixer bowl, cut butter and cream cheese into 1 cup flour until mixture forms a smooth dough.
Roll out to fit a 9-inch pie or quiche pan.
Freeze 10 minutes.
In large saucepan, place spinach.
Cook over medium heat a few minutes until wilted.
Drain and chop.
Drain well on paper towel.
In a large bowl, combine spinach with the 2 tablespoons flour.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into prepared pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until set in the center.
Makes 1 (9-inch) quiche.

title: nippy clam spread
directions: Place all ingredients in blender, cover and run on high speed until thoroughly combined.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving to allow the flavors to blend.

title: orange-fennel spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and crumble the ground beef; set aside.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon beef fat.
In same pan, fry onion until limp; add garlic and fry until limp.
Add mushrooms and fry until limp.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, red wine and seasonings.
Simmer.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together whipped cream and cream cheese.
Add sugar, marshmallows, pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze 4 hours.

title: easy beef burgundy
directions: Place all ingredients in a 3 to 4-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and bake 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Do not open lid or stir before checking for doneness at 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 6 to 8.

title: carnation fudge(makes 2 pounds)
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Bring to full boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until marshmallows melt and blend. Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: orange chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces with salt, garlic powder, paprika, pepper, tarragon and thyme.
Place in a shallow baking pan, skin side down.
Combine the freshly grated peels, juices and water; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 40 minutes. Turn the chicken and continue baking.
Baste with pan juices once or twice until done, in about 35 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place soup, chicken, onion and broth in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and pepper and butter until crumbly.
Add milk and spoon into casserole.
Bake 30-40 minutes at 350°.

title: randee's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender (not too long).
Combine all ingredients.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain well.
Mix vinegar and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Put pickles in freezer containers or small plastic margarine tubs, leaving 1 inch headspace.
Freeze immediately.

title: snickerdoodles(pennsylvania dutch cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in whole egg and egg yolk.
Sift flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Mix into batter.
Fold in nuts and raisins.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine and cook beef and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly. Put in a casserole dish.
Put thin strips of cheese on top of beef mixture.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: summer chiller
directions: Cut lemons, limes and oranges and squeeze juice thoroughly. Add cranberry juice, sugar and water to fill 1/2 gallon pitcher. Pour over ice or blend with ice in blender for icee.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook ingredients in pan on stove. Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, blanch cabbage leaves and when cool enough, fill with meat ingredients, enough to roll cabbage leaves.
Place in a dish large enough so they won't come apart.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce over them.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Baste once in awhile so they won't dry out.
You can use this as soon as you make it, unless you want to let it sit overnight.

title: nutty o's
directions: In a large saucepan heat sugar, syrup and butter until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread onto greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes.
Stir to loosen from pan.
Store in airtight container.

title: french silk chocolate pie with raspberry sauce
directions: Spread raspberries in a thin layer across the bottom of the pie crust.
Heat milk to just below the boiling point (I use the microwave).
Put milk, chocolate, egg and sugar into blender.
Add the hot milk and immediately blend at low speed for 1 minute. Pour into crust over raspberries.
Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: boiled cider pie(a shaker recipe)
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Form a decorative edge and freeze.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan, simmer boiled cider, butter, maple sugar or syrup and sugar, water and salt for several minutes.
Transfer to a large bowl and let cool slightly. Blend egg yolks with liquids, then fold in the whites gently, but thoroughly.
Pour into chilled pie shell and bake for 30 to 40 minutes
until set.
Give pie a generous dust of nutmeg.
Serve cooled with lightly sweetened whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, spinach, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and the egg. Spread 1/3 cup cheese mixture on each lasagna noodle; then roll up.
Pour 1/2 cup pasta sauce over the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange lasagna rolls, seam sides down, in baking dish.
Top with the remaining sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake 35 minutes or until hot.
Garnish as desired.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: Saute bacon until crisp; drain off fat.
Add chopped onion and saute for 2 minutes.
Add all other ingredients except potatoes and cook until slightly thick.
Add potatoes and blend well. Remove from heat and serve warm.

title: ting-a-ling(haystacks)
directions: In large saucepan, melt chips over low heat, stirring constantly.*
Remove from heat and quickly stir in noodles and peanuts, making sure all ingredients are coated evenly. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. Chill until firm. Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Cream sour cream and cream cheese with a mixer.
Stir in salt, sugar and marshmallows.
Stir in drained fruit.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch container and freeze.

title: pasedini
directions: Mix cheese, bread crumbs and eggs.
Form large balls with this mixture.
Press each ball through a pasta maker.
The holes in the pasta maker should be 1/2-inch in diameter.
Spread noodles on trays overnight to dry.
Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Drop in noodles and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve with additional cheese on the side to sprinkle on soup.
Serves 15.
Mange! Mange!

title: ingrid's hot strawberry sundae
directions: Put strawberries in saucepan with sugar and vanilla extract. Cook on low heat.
Add brandy or brandy flavoring, if desired. Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Scoop vanilla ice cream into serving dishes.
Spoon strawberry sauce over ice cream.
Top with whipped cream.
Serve while sauce is hot.

title: sausage delight
directions: Start cooking spaghetti.
In separate frying pan, saute sausages for 5 minutes.
Add bell pepper, garlic and lemon pepper. Saute another 7 minutes or so.
When sausages are golden brown, remove them from the frying pan onto a cutting board.
Slice sausages into pieces and put back into frying pan.
Remove spaghetti and drain.
Add to frying pan.
Add a couple of tablespoons of olive oil to frying pan and saute a couple more minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Put mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Lay bacon strips across top.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes or until beans are hot, bubbling, and of the consistency desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Grease pans and flour them.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch layer pans or one 13 x 9-inch. Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy 5 minutes on high speed.
Sift flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix with water and vanilla.
Use low speed until thoroughly mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: light bright shrimp salad
directions: Combine shrimp, celery, green pepper and onion.
Pour in oil and toss until all ingredients are lightly coated.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Continue tossing until well mixed. Arrange 2 slices of pineapple on each of 4 lettuce lined salad plates.
Spoon shrimp mixture over pineapple.
Makes 4 servings of 250 calories each.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender; drain.
Heat oven to 325 degrees.
Coat 8 x 12-inch baking dish with cooking spray.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth. Add peanut butter.
Beat well. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into cooled pie shells.
Sprinkle chopped peanuts over pie.
Chill at least 2 to 4 hours; overnight is better.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put oatmeal and wheat germ in mixing bowl.
Stir.
Add vegetable oil and honey.
Spread mixture on cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and add whatever extra ingredients you choose (except raisins).
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in raisins, if used.
Let cool, stirring while it cools.
Store in a container with a tight fitting cover.
Makes 4 cups.

title: crabmeat puffs
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on English muffins.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cut each muffin into quarters.
Makes 48 pieces.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool completely.
Beat together cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar until sugar dissolves.
Refrigerate for 8 minutes.
Spread over pretzels.
Melt gelatin in hot water.
Let cool; add strawberries.
Pour over cheese spread.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken club brunch ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Add parsley and onion to mayonnaise mixture; mix well. In another bowl, add chicken, bacon, 3/4 cup of cheese and 1/3 cup of mayonnaise mixture; mix well.
Unroll crescent dough; separate into 16 triangles.
Arrange triangles in a circle on 13-inch round baking stone with wide ends of triangle overlapping in the center and points toward the outside.
Scoop chicken mixture evenly onto widest end of each triangle.
Bring outside points of triangle up over filling and tuck under wide ends of dough at center of ring. (Filling won't be completely covered.)
Cut tomato slices in half; place 1/2 over filling between openings of ring.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Cut bell pepper in half; remove inside membranes and seeds.
Fill bell peppers with remaining mayonnaise mixture.
Place in center of ring.
Arrange lettuce around peppers.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel candy bars
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Spread into a 13 x 12-inch pan. Bake for about 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: souperburger sandwiches
directions: In skillet cook beef and onion until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add soup, pepper and mustard; heat through, stirring often.
Serve on buns.

title: onion gravy
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix onion soup mix with 1 1/2 cups of water.
Bring to boil, then simmer covered, stirring occasionally for 8 minutes.
Stir in flour blended with remaining 1/2 cup of water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring constantly, until gravy is thickened, for about 2 minutes.
Makes 1 3/4 cups of gravy.

title: cottage cheese cocoa cake
directions: Press cottage cheese through a sieve.
Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Blend in cottage cheese and blend thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each egg.
Mix buttermilk alternately with flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Stir in chopped walnuts.
Turn into well buttered and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Press graham cracker crumbs into pan. Pour can of milk over graham cracker crumbs. Sprinkle chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and nuts over mixture. Sprinkle coconut over top. Bake for approximately 15 minutes or until coconut browns.

title: spaghetti with anchovy and clam sauce
directions: Butterfly boneless chicken breast (press or beat flat, 1/2-inch thick).
Place slice of Swiss cheese and baked ham in center.
Add spoonful of chopped spinach (thawed and slightly sauteed with garlic and olive oil).
Roll up and place in Pyrex baking dish.
Pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup, mixed with one can white wine.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 4-inch) loaf pans.
Into a mixing bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.
In second mixing bowl, cream butter until it is pale yellow and light; add honey, mixing thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add lemon zest and all herbs, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients in thirds, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Mix only to incorporate; do not overmix.

title: weight watcher cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix half of pineapple, half of cherry pie mix and half of pudding in bowl.

title: party mints
directions: Cream the cream cheese, adding powdered sugar gradually.
Add flavoring.
Mix until stiff enough to mold.
Add coloring.
Pour into desired candy mold.
Candy may be frozen.
If extract is used, use 1/4 teaspoon.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add cooked pumpkin, milk, eggs and butter.
Mix ground cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and cloves with flour and sugar.
Cook on medium heat on stove, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell when thick and cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
May spread on bread or crackers.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add pumpkin.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and spices.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture; beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes. Cool 15 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or Butter Rum Sauce.

title: blueberry tart
directions: Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour blueberry pie filling over mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts or crushed graham crackers.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt. With wire whisk, stir in milk until smooth; stir in rice. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and begins to boil, about 10 minutes. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. In small bowl, beat eggs. Slowly add about 1/2 cup hot pudding mixture into eggs while stirring constantly with spoon. Slowly pour egg mixture into pudding mixture, stirring rapidly to prevent eggs from lumping. Add raisins, cinnamon and nutmeg. Return pan to low heat and cook, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes, until very thick and just starting to bubble. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Serve warm or chilled. Top with whipped topping, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: marion hogan's drop cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, granulated sugar and Crisco; add eggs gradually and add vanilla.
Bring raisins and water to a boil, boil 2 minutes, cool and add baking soda.
Mix together dry ingredients and add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: healthy bean salad
directions: Mix all the above ingredients and let sit in the refrigerator for a day before serving.
It is delicious.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Add salt, pepper and mayonnaise to taste.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together the shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg thoroughly.
Stir in bananas and sour milk or buttermilk.
(To sour milk, add 1 teaspoon vinegar.)
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and chopped nuts.
Stir in flour mixture with rest of ingredients.
Line a greased 5 x 10 x 13-inch bread pan with 2 thicknesses of plain paper.
Grease the paper.
Pour in batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut cream 4 layer delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans and press down with fork in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until edges are browned.
Cool.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add pepper and onion, mixing well.
Add eggs and oil.
When well mixed, add corn, milk and water.
Stir well.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a large pan or skillet.
Add cheese.
Pour on rest of bread mixture.
Bake at 450° until brown.
If desired, leave out jalapeno peppers.

title: easy chili and old-fashioned corn bread(serves 4)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly coat an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with cooking spray; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; set aside.
Pour margarine into small bowl; whisk together with milk and egg.
Add to cornmeal mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into pan; bake 20 minutes or until bread is golden and top springs back when touched.
Cut into 8 squares.
Prepare chili according to package directions.
Remove to serving plates and serve with corn bread.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook
spaghetti
in chicken broth reserved from cooking fryers.
Saute
onion and peppers in margarine.
Mix in chicken, peas,
pimento,
tomatoes
and
chilies and cheese cut in chunks. Heat until cheese melts.
Stir in spaghetti and broth mixture. Pour
into	three
13 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Freeze two casseroles and
bake
the other at 325° until hot and bubbly. Garnish with cheese triangles.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Simmer celery and onions in covered pan until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over
rolled
oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
In
the
meanwhile,
cream
butter with white sugar, brown
sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well and add the oatmeal mixture.
Sift
the flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon; add to the mixture.
Beat
until smooth.
Pour in greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch deep oblong pan.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Broiled Frosting.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time. Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Add flour mixture and milk.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: falafel(fried bean cakes)
directions: Soak chickpeas overnight.
Drain.
Combine peas, onions, garlic, parsley.
Grind with meat grinder or beat until almost creamy.
Add salt, cumin and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
When ready to fry, mix in baking soda.
Shape into small patties.
Fry in deep hot oil (electric wok works well) until light brown and crisp.
Serve hot with fresh tomato slices and lettuce leaves and sliced onions in pita bread.

title: ella lee wigals lye soap(1960)
directions: Dissolve lye in 1 quart of cold water.
Melt grease and cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve Borax in 1/2 cup water.
Slowly pour the lye in the grease.
Stir until thick as honey, then add Borax and 1 cup ammonia.
Stir until thick and pour into square pan.
I cut it when it hardens.
Use in 4 weeks.

title: carob brownies
directions: Beat butter, honey and carob powder together.
Beat in eggs. Stir remaining ingredients and beat in.
Pour into well-greased, foil-lined 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° just 25 minutes.
Turn on wire rack to cool.
While still slightly warm, cut desired size pieces.

title: golden chicken bake
directions: In 2-quart baking dish, arrange chicken breasts, skin side down.
Mix water, soups and melted oleo.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hot tots dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Place drained meat in baking dish.
Pour soup over meat mixture and cover with potato tots.
Bake about 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook sausage and onions, then drain.
Add 2 tablespoons breadcrumbs and mix well.
Add cream cheese, sauerkraut, parsley and mustard.
Chill.
Make into small balls and dip into bowl of flour, then into milk and egg mixture and then into bowl of breadcrumbs.
Fry in hot oil until browned.

title: blueberry muffins(yields 12 muffins)
directions: Mix together milk, oil and egg in a large bowl.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in 1 cup of blueberries.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes; cool.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Trim cabbage; wash, cut in quarters, remove core and cut again.
Place water and bouillon cubes in Dutch oven.
Add cabbage, cut up potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 25 minutes; stir.
Lay slices of corned beef on top, cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Turn off heat.
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.
Can be reheated nicely.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: scented pinecones
directions: The amount of paraffin or wax needed depends on the number of scented pinecones you make.
Start with just a few to see how much wax is needed.
Melt paraffin.
(Set a small coffee can inside a large pot to use double boiler style.)
Put 2 to 3 in water in larger pot.
Heat pan until water boils and wax melts.
Add food coloring after it's melted.
Place cupcake liners in the tins; put a 4-inch piece of string in each liner.
Fit the pinecones into the cupcake liner.
If the cones are fresh, you will smell the scent from the cones when lit.
If cones are older, add a drop of clove oil or desired scent of your choice to melted paraffin.
Carefully pour melted wax over pinecones into paper liners.
Don't take off liners until the wax cools, at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: hot dog chile
directions: Boil hamburger and drain. Add catsup, salt, pepper, onion powder and chili powder. Add a little water and simmer.

title: zucchini *
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes and bring to boil.
Add salt, pepper, marjoram and oregano.
Stir well, breaking up tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add zucchini and simmer until barely tender if making in advance for later reheating.
If serving immediately, simmer until it is to your taste.

title: hamburger snacks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except buns.
Spread 1/2 inch thick on hamburger buns.
Spread to edge to keep from burning.
Broil for 8 minutes or to desired doneness.

title: turkey cutlets with mushrooms and sherry
directions: Combine the flour, salt and pepper on a plate.
Press the turkey cutlets into the mixture, coating them evenly and shaking off any excess.
Set aside.

title: bread of life
directions: Be prepared to walk through Heaven's gate.
Repent now, don't wait until it's too late.
Eternal life no cup can measure. Angels waiting with your treasure.
Don't give up the Bread of Life.
Onward to God's table strive.
Faith and hope fills a big, big pan, but love is the greatest food to Man.
In our church cookbook, we did our best for you, each recipe to test.
Eat and drink, give God the praise, be filled with His blessings every day.

title: cream cheese poundcake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar and continue creaming until light and fluffy.
