Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla extract. Add flour in 1/3 portions at a time, beating until smooth. Slowly stir in Dream Whip.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Once cool, may be glazed, if desired.

title: creamy mocha mousse
directions: Stir instant coffee into boiling water in small heavy saucepan until completely dissolved.
Add chocolate; place over low heat, stirring just until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Whisk egg yolks into chocolate mixture one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in brandy.
Beat egg whites in medium bowl until foamy; beat in sugar gradually, one tablespoon at a time, forming soft peaks.
Fold in chocolate mixture until no streaks of white remain. Spoon into 8 parfait glasses.
Chill 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped cream rosette.
Add a candied rosebud and mint leaf if you wish.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and salt; beat well.
Add flour.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Dip in egg whites, then nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press down centers with thumb.
Fill indention with preserves.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add mixture of oil, milk, eggs and molasses.
Next, add fruits, nuts and remaining ingredients. Bake in 300° to 325° oven for an hour at least.
Soak cheesecloth in orange juice, wrap cake in cheesecloth and set in refrigerator for 48 hours (2 days).

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt for 10 minutes.
Drain noodles.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Whip cream until thick; add egg yolks and beat until foamy. Add sugar and vanilla and beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with beaten egg white to first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips last.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Remove with spatula to cooling racks.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or less.

title: coconut - pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add crushed pineapple.
Bake in a greased sheet pan 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix ingredients for 30 seconds on high in a blender.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Let chill one hour before serving.

title: green pea and green bean salad(a great "make ahead" dish)
directions: Drain green beans and peas.
Chop celery, bell pepper and onion.
Combine vegetables.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil together. Pour over vegetables and stir.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Mix and dip onion rings into batter before frying.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Drain.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add garlic.
Cook until tender. Add flour and slightly brown.
Gradually add milk while stirring. Add cream cheese and 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Pour sauce over cooked fettuccine and sprinkle remaining 1 cup Parmesan cheese on top.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Slice zucchini real thin.
Spray a big pan with Pam.
Mix bread crumbs with pepper (small amount); put in a Baggie.
Take a few slices of zucchini at a time and shake in the Baggie.
Put them on a baking tray.
Then put Parmesan cheese on each slice and then put a little margarine on each slice.
Broil until brown; then turn over.
Make sure to add margarine.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook squash and onion in boiling salted water; cover for 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Stir together soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots, then fold in squash and onions. Spread half stuffing mix in bottom of 12 x 7-inch baking pan. Spoon vegetable mixture over stuffing and sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peas and macaroni
directions: In a saucepan, put the oil and cut up onion.
Cook until the onion browns a little on the edges.
Now add the tomato sauce and 1 can of water.
Also add the can of peas liquid too.
Cook for 1 hour on a low heat.
(You can add the red pepper now, if desired.) Boil some water and put broken macaroni in to cook until done. Pour the peas and sauce into a bowl and put the drained macaroni on top.
Mix up and enjoy.
You have a fast and easy supper done. Serve a salad and bread with this meal.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add beans and dressing; let simmer.
Put Doritos on a plate.
Top with tossed salad, beef and bean mixture and grated cheese.

title: bean dip and chips
directions: Cook 1 to 2 hours slowly in crock-pot.
Serve warm with chips.

title: froot loop cookies
directions: Melt the white chocolate in a double boiler.
Pour over Rice Krispies and Froot Loops.
Mix slowly.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool at room temperature.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Melt milk and chocolate; add coconut and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars and eggs.
Add milk, vanilla and dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. These cookies stay soft.

title: special "k" candy bars
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together 3 seconds.
Add peanut butter and beat until smooth.
Pour over cereal and spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt chocolate chips and ice candy with them. Cool.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Separate the eggs, adding yolks to sugar and butter.
Next, add the flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and milk. Beat egg whites and fold in. Add blueberries. Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain. Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Place slices of bread on top of cheese. (May tear into small pieces.)
Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let set in refrigerator, covered, overnight.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until top of bread is browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork steaks
directions: Over medium heat, lay pork steaks in skillet; salt and pepper to taste.
Add very little water.
Slice onion and mango and lay across pork steaks.
Cook about 30 minutes, covered.
Add tomato sauce and just warm over medium heat.

title: crock-pot beef roast
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks.
Cut carrots into slices.
Rinse beef roast; season with salt and pepper.
Place all of the ingredients, except gravy mix, into crock-pot.
Add 2 quarts of water and the gravy mix.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook the rotini noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add salad dressing, olives, pepperoni, Parmesan and Cheddar cheese to noodles.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.
tags: Wish Bone Italian Robust salad dressing

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions; drain.
Brown sausage and beef with onion and pepper; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese and herbs.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, toss ziti with meat sauce. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: wild rice and pepper salad
directions: Prepare rice; cool.
Mix the salad dressing, oil, black pepper and lemon peel.
Add rice and remaining ingredients; mix lightly. Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald tomatoes, peel, core and slice in chunks in large kettle.
Cook 15 minutes; drain off half (about 6 cups) the juice. Add celery, onion and peppers; simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Tie cinnamon in cloth; add with remaining ingredients and 1/4 cup salt.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together and put in refrigerator.
Let stand a day before serving.
Makes a large dish, and keeps for many days.

title: basque garbanzo casserole
directions: Saute pepperoni; remove with slotted spoon.
Cut chicken into 2-inch pieces and brown in pan drippings.
Remove.
Saute leek and garlic.
Stir in carrots and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in cabbage, cooking 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring to blend well.
Spoon into a 12-cup baking dish with chicken and pepperoni. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: aunt teri's cheese puffs
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Fold in the pineapple and Cool Whip. Fill cookies.
Refrigerate overnight on cookie sheet or tray.
Do not cover.

title: pressure canned green beans
directions: Wash,
string
and break or cut green beans into 1-inch pieces.
Pack
tightly
into
jars, leaving within 1/2-inch of top of	jar.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to each pint or 1 teaspoon salt to a	quart.	After
packing	beans in jar, add salt and fill within
1/2-inch
of
top of jar with hot water.
Put on lid, that has been setting in hot water.
Screw on cap tightly and
place into
pressure
canner.
Most
canners will hold 7 quarts
or
8 pints.
After putting jars into canner, add 3/4 full
of
hot water.
Place on lid;
tighten down securely and place
on	gauze. Time after it rises with steam and jiggles, 20
minutes
for pints and 25 minutes for quarts.
Let canner cool
down
before removing lid.
Remove from canner and place cloth over jars; let stand to seal for 24 hours, then place on shelves
or in cabinet. Date lid with magic marker; will keep for years.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease a Bundt pan, then sprinkle bottom and sides
with
sugar.
Pour cake batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out
clean
(start
testing
at 45 minutes).
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Cool on cake rack.

title: 3-way cajun baked beans
directions: Drain beans and combine with other ingredients in large crock-pot.
Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or place in aluminum roasting pan 3 to 4 inches deep (15 3/4 x 11 3/8 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.
May be served hot or cold.
Serves about 20 to 25 people.

title: apple bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and add eggs.
Mix.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Spread 1/2 dough into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread applesauce over dough mixture.
Put remaining dough on top.
Spread.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tofu spinach parmesan
directions: Cut the tofu into halves or quarters.
Beat egg, dip tofu into egg, then into bread crumbs.
Saute in olive oil until brown on both sides.
Pour 1/3 of spaghetti sauce into a casserole dish and place breaded tofu on top; set aside.
Wash spinach well and steam ever so slightly.
Drain well and place on tofu.
Cut Mozzarella cheese into cubes and place on top of each piece of tofu.
Cover with the rest of sauce and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with fettucini, salad and garlic bread.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and rinse in lemon juice.
Fold in all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serve with crackers (Ritz, Sociables).

title: peanut butter pie(makes 2)
directions: Beat cream cheese; blend in powdered sugar.
Add peanut butter, milk and Cool Whip.
Beat together; pour into 2 graham cracker crust pie shells.

title: pasta with clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and butter in a large skillet.
Saute onions and garlic, covered, until soft (about 30 minutes) over very low heat. Add basil, oregano and red pepper flakes and simmer for about 5 more minutes.
Add parsley; cover and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add clams, clam juice and wine.
Simmer uncovered over low heat for 10 minutes.
If sauce is too thin, add a little arrowroot mixed 1/2 and 1/2 with water to thicken.
Simmer until thickened.
Serve over pasta.

title: sandies
directions: Mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours.
Shape in small balls and bake at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
While browning beef, cook noodles.
After both are cooked, combine all ingredients in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: ellie's wine punch(prepare a double recipe for a large punch bowl)
directions: Combine syrup, wine and apple juice in punch bowl.
Float a decorated or plain chunk of ice in bowl when serving.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix crushed cereal, butter and sugar.
Pat mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: sliced apples
directions: Place in baking dish. Dot with margarine and bake at 325° until tender.

title: cocoa drops
directions: Add first 3 ingredients.
Beat well together.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Mix cocoa together with flour and add to mixture. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spicy crock-pot chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and place in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Serves 4.

title: pepperoni quiche
directions: Grease tart pans and press crust in pans.
Beat eggs and cream.
Stir in cheese and pepperoni.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: saucy chicken and asparagus
directions: Partially cook asparagus; drain.
Place in a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
In a skillet, brown chicken in oil on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken over asparagus.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, sour cream, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Boil raisins for 10 minutes; drain and put into an unbaked pie shell.
Add all mixed ingredients; pour over raisins. Bake 1 hour in moderate oven.

title: beef-noodle bake
directions: Brown meat; add mushrooms and green peppers.
Cook noodles in salt water.
Drain.
In large baking dish, layer meat, noodles and cheese.
Repeat.
Pour sauce over top and cover with more cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: slow cooker barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high (300°) for 8 hours.
Then with wire whisk stir mixture until meat is shredded.
Serve on warm rolls or bread.

title: pork 'n' beef bake
directions: Make 2 servings of each pork steak by cutting along one side of the bone.
Trim away excess fat.
Trim the round steak of skin and fibrous material.
Cut into serving-size portions and tenderize with meat mallet on both sides.
In plastic bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Shake pieces of meat to coat and brown in hot oil.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Put into lightly greased Bundt pan.
Take leftover cinnamon and sugar mixture and mix with melted butter and vanilla.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn out onto serving plate.
Pull off in bite size pieces.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix the salt with the cabbage; let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess moisture.
Add the remaining vegetables; set aside. Combine and boil the vinegar, water, mustard seed, celery seed and sugar; boil for 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over slaw; put into freezer containers and freeze.

title: jello salad
directions: Boil jello (no water) and pineapple together for 3 minutes. Let cool.
Add cottage cheese, whipped cream and nuts.
Pour into dish and chill.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together real good.
Add lemon juice last.
Pour into crusts and chill.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat a deep pot over medium to medium high heat.
Work next to the stove to slice onions.
Add oil and butter to the pot.
Add onions to the pot as you slice them.
When all the onions are in the pot, season with salt and pepper and 1 teaspoon fresh thyme. Cook onions 15 to 18 minutes, stirring frequently, until tender, sweet and caramel colored.
Add bay leaf and sherry to the pot and deglaze the pan drippings.
Add 6 cups stock and cover pot to bring soup up to a quick boil.
Arrange 4 small, deep soup bowls or crocks on a cookie sheet.
Preheat broiler to high.
Once soup reaches a boil, ladle it into bowls.

Float toasty crusty bread on soup and cover each bowl with a mound of cheese; sprinkle remaining fresh thyme on cheese and place cookie sheet with soup bowls on it under hot broiler until cheese melts and bubbles.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine water and butter.
Boil together until it comes to a hard boil; then add flour and salt.
Stir until ball is formed. Cool.
Add one egg at a time until all four eggs have been used, stirring well after each egg is added.
Divide dough in 12 parts. Drop on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes. Makes 12 large puffs.
Fill with cream filling or whipped cream.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in a large bowl.
Cover with vinegar and water. Make a net (cheesecloth) of cloves and bay leaves and place in the vinegar water.
Jab meat with fork.
Slice onions over meat. Marinate for 3 to 4 days, turning meat daily.
Cook roast as you would any beef roast.
Use vinegar water and onions to make an onion gravy.

title: double cream chocolate cake
directions: Cook milk, cornstarch and half and half until thick as pudding.
Refrigerate until cold.
Cream butter, margarine, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add milk and cornstarch mixture.
Beat continuously 5 minutes.
Frost cake.
Put in refrigerator.

title: desperation dip
directions: Stir mustard into mayonnaise until smooth.
Cover and chill. Serve with fat, salty pretzels.

title: fresh veggie salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Drain olives, cube cheeses and chop green onions.
Place in a large bowl.
Add dressing and toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate. Before serving, toss gently and top with Bacos.
Serves 12.

title: orange pudding
directions: Squeeze orange and pour juice over 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Stir to dissolve and set aside.
Grind or cut up raisins.
Cream together remainder of sugar and butter.
Add egg and soda.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Combine with raisins. Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex dish or pan. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
While hot, pour sweetened orange juice over cake.
When cool, tear up cake into small pieces and fold into Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.
Can be served as cake slices with Cool Whip.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together 1 stick margarine (melted) and the graham cracker crumbs.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: italian pork pasta sauce
directions: Trim roast and cut into bite sized pieces.
Brown on all sides in skillet.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil in large saucepan until onion is transparent; do not brown.
Add tomato paste and water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Add pork.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or to desired consistency.
Serve over shell macaroni with salad and garlic bread.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
May add hard-boiled eggs 30 minutes before end of cooking time if desired.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: roast venison
directions: Rinse venison roast in cold water.
Dry with paper towels. Rub the ham fat over all the roast.
Squeeze lemon juice over venison.
Slice onion into rings.
Separate and lay onion over top of roast.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper and salt.
Pour the cup of water into roaster pan.
Cover with roaster lid.
Refrigerate overnight (12 hours).

title: skroodles
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup (can) of milk.
Cut Velveeta cheese into chunks.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all together.
Cook until cheese melts. Yummy!

title: manwich snack
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain off all fat. Stir in Manwich and heat through, stirring constantly.
When ready to serve, place meat mixture in individual bowls.
Sprinkle cheese over the meat, followed by a dab of sour cream on top.
Use Tostitos to dip and eat.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour gradually.
Add pop and flavoring.
Beat for 3 minutes on high.
Turn oven to 350° and cook until done, about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Mix sugar and pears; let sit 1 hour.
Put oil in pear mixture. Beat eggs and pour in pears.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to pear mixture slowly.
Stir with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bake in tube pan.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, then add remaining ingredients until smooth. Put a vanilla wafer in bottom of each paper tin.
Fill paper tins 2/3 way up.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Combine cake mix with applesauce, eggs, lemon, orange and vanilla extracts, mixing well.
Toss cherries, pineapple, dates and nuts with flour to coat.
Stir fruit and nuts into cake mixture, mixing well.
Turn mixture into 2 greased and wax paper lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 275° for 1 3/4 hours approximately.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack.
Cool completely before removing wax paper.
Can be frozen.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers and cheese.
Put into a greased casserole; add cheese.
In another bowl mix melted butter and crushed Ritz crackers.
Top casserole and bake about 15 minutes or until cheese melts and crackers brown.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook sausage until lightly browned; drain well.
Spoon into pie plate, topping sausage with hash browns, then cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and pepper; pour over cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: scottish jelly oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Add flour, oatmeal, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Make dough into balls and press down center with floured fingers.
Fill with jelly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes four dozen.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; pat mixture into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes (save 1/4 cup for top). Meanwhile, beat cheese and sugar smooth; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top. Bake 30 minutes or more until set.
Cool on wire rack.
When cool, cut in 2-inch squares and then diagonally.
Makes 32.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hershey cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add syrup, flour and milk (alternating).
Stir in Hershey bars (melted over low heat) and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg. Add alternately with cooked apples using juice with apples. Gently fold in raisins and nuts. Cook in tube pan at 250° for 2 hours.

title: fried scampi
directions: Wash prawns in cold water.
Remove tiny legs.
Peel off shells and devein prawns.
Rinse in cold water, then pat dry with absorbent paper.

title: stained glass jello
directions: Set each jello in separate bowls, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until firm.
Combine 1 cup pineapple juice and 1/4 cup sugar.
Heat until dissolved.
Remove from heat and dissolve 1 small package lemon jello in juice.
Chill until syrupy.
Whip 1 cup cream firm.
Add to syrup; fold gently.
Cut jello into small squares and toss with dressing.
Save some squares for garnish.

title: oven baked chicken(fake fried chicken, one of lisa trapani's favorites)
directions: Use rolling pin to crush crackers and Melba toast on a piece of waxed paper.
Place the flour on a small plate.
Pour the Egg Beaters on another small plate.
Pour the liquid Butter Buds or chicken broth into a large nonstick skillet.
Turn stove on low to medium.
Coat the chicken breast with flour.
Dip them in Egg Beaters, then roll them in the cracker crumbs to coat well.
In the skillet, cook until both sides are golden.
Place on a baking sheet prepared with a nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until crisp.
Serves 6.
Nutrient value per serving:
238 calories, 17 g carbohydrates, 3.5 g fat, 31 g protein, 73 mg. cholesterol.
For variety, add 1 tablespoon nonfat Parmesan cheese to the cracker mixture.
You can also pour on some barbecue sauce or grated nonfat cheese to make the chicken more flavorful, but not fatter.

title: phillip's honey-dijon dressing
directions: Shake ingredients in a tightly covered container. Always shake before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken
directions: Method 1:
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Turn heat to 425° and continue cooking for 15 minutes.

title: stroganoff sauce
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart pan, over medium heat, in hot butter, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, sour cream, milk and paprika. Heat through, stirring often.
Serve over vegetables, beef or rice.

title: yorkshire popovers
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl.
Let set in bowl for 1/2 hour.
Pour 1/4 cup of the mixture in the 6 sections of a muffin tin.
Add 1 teaspoon of meat grease into each one.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses get soft (room temperature). Mix all ingredients together; form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate.
Before serving,
let set at room temperature for a while.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add salt and sugar; continue to beat.
Fold in milk, half and half, and vanilla.
At this point, you can add 1 1/2 c. sweetened peaches or strawberries.
Pour mixture into ice cream freezer.
Layer ice and salt beginning with 6 c. of crushed ice and 1/4 c. of salt.
When the ice cream is frozen, remove cover and dasher, scraping the ice cream back into the can.
Blend the soft with the firmer portion of ice cream.
Place aluminum foil across the top of the can, replace cover, and put cork into cover hole.
Pour off brine and pack contained with more salt and ice using a greater portion of salt than before.
Wrap container in heavy towel or newspapers to insulate and let stand an hour or two until ice cream has hardened.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Place in refrigerator until first 3 ingredients begin to gel. Add Cool Whip and nuts.

title: miniature reubens
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; arrange bread slices on cookie sheet and spread dressing on one side of bread.
On each slice add some beef, cheese and sauerkraut.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and bread is toasted.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Select small potatoes and peel. Cook whole until done. Drain off water. Add milk about 1-inch above potatoes. Add 1/2 stick butter; salt and pepper to taste. Let this heat slowly so as not to burn the milk. Mix plain flour, about 2 tablespoons, in 1/2 cup of milk. Shake until smooth. Slowly add to very hot potatoes, a little at a time, until milk gets as thick as you like. This is good for the small new potatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup and
sugar;
add
melted butter.
Mix in eggs and vanilla; let
stand
for
hour.	Place
pecan pieces in 9-inch pie shell.	Pour in filling and cover with pecan pieces turned right side	up.
Pie
is prettier when pecan pieces are placed in a
starburst
pattern.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Add butter and work in dry ingredients with knife or pastry blender.
Add well beaten egg, vanilla and half of the sour cream, cutting liquid into dry ingredients with knife or blender.
Add remainder of sour cream to form soft dough.
Refrigerate 1 hour or longer.
Roll dough.
Cut cookies.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 310° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: out of this world dessert
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thickened.
While hot, add cherry jello; cool.
Add nuts and bananas.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain. Chop olives, green pepper and tomatoes. Mix well. Add dressing and celery seed. Chill for 4 hours. Serve cold.

title: poppy seed tea bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat and pour into 2 or 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into the pie crust. Chill for 30 minutes or longer.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Make two layers of each in 7 1/2 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Spread 1 to 1 1/2 cups mayonnaise over the top (or salad dressing) mixed with a little cream.
Seal tightly with Saran Wrap.
Let stand overnight.
Just before serving, toss slightly.
Top with 4 to 6 ounces of shredded cheese and Bac*Os.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green pepper, celery, onion and peas in a large bowl.
Spread mayonnaise and sugar on top. Sprinkle cheese, then bacon on top.
Cover tightly for 24 hours.
Great for busy day schedules!

title: squash patties
directions: Mix squash and onion.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add flour, corn meal, pepper, cheese and egg.
Form into patties and fry.

title: pie crusts
directions: Mix flour, salt and lard until crumbly, then add egg, vinegar and water.

title: round steak
directions: In 1 tablespoon oil, brown steak until done; remove from pan. Add 1 tablespoon oil and saute onion, celery, garlic and mushrooms at high temperature (stirring constantly) until light brown; remove from pan. Add cornstarch and slightly brown. Stir in 1/2 of the chicken broth; stir. Add all cooked ingredients and cook together. Cook 2 cups rice with 1/2 of the chicken broth and water.
Ready to serve.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Slice banana into bottom of crust.
Drain pineapple and mix with Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice; set back in refrigerator. Cover each pie with 1/2 Cool Whip.
Sprinkle each pie with coconut, cherries and nuts.

title: eggs poached in white wine
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add wine; slip in eggs, salt and pepper.
Poach until whites are nearly firm.
Sprinkle crumbled Blue cheese over eggs.
Heat until melted.
Serve on hot buttered toast.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together, adding buttermilk last.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: boxed macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil water and add noodles as directed on side of box.
Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Add butter and milk.
Then add packaged cheese mix.
Stir well until cheese is dissolved.
Serve hot and with a fork.

title: high energizer(breakfast)
directions: Place ingredients in blender in order given.
Blend for 1 minute, or until smooth.
Great for breakfast or anytime.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: easy savory baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake covered in greased casserole at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook raisins; drain and set aside.
Cook until thickened the remaining ingredients.
Add raisins and pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue and bake until meringue is brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, drain and squeeze out excess water.
Mix all ingredients together; chill at least 6 hours before serving.

title: t.v. cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk in a bowl.
Pour mixture over melted butter.
Do not stir!
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: milky way bar cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs. Cut up and melt candy bars. Add to creamed mixture. Sift together flour and soda. Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture. Add nuts and vanilla. Bake in tube pan at 350° until done.

title: 2 egg yellow cake
directions: Sift
together
flour,
baking
powder and salt.
Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one
at
a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.
Add
dry
ingredients
alternately with milk and water, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch
cake
pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake tests
done.
Cool in pan on rack.
Makes 16 servings.

title: microwave marmalade
directions: Cut oranges in large pieces; place in blender or food processor.
Use everything but the seeds.
Whirl until evenly chopped.
Measure fruit and juice; place in non-metal bowl.
Add equal amount of sugar.
Stir.
Cook, uncovered, until thick as you like, 6 to 8 minutes.
Should cling to metal spoon.
It thickens as it cools.
As marmalade cooks, stir well every 2 minutes. Refrigerate or freeze for later use.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: crab quiche
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until golden and soft.
Spoon alternate layers of crab, cheese and onion/celery into pie shell. Beat together eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour into filled pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until firm, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salted water for about 8 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown beef in small amount of shortening.
To the meat mixture, add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, parsley flakes, oregano and garlic salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese crescent bars
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Set aside egg white.
Place one can of rolls in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over rolls.
Spread 1 can of pie filling over cream cheese.
Place second can of rolls on top and brush with egg white.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water.
Add water, just to gather flour mixture together.
Knead dough; do not overwork dough.
Take small balls of dough and roll out.
Place on heated griddle.
Cook on each side for approximately 2 minutes, or until it is golden color.

title: pot roast of beef
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pat into surface of 4 to 5 pound piece of beef (chuck, shoulders, rump or round).
Heat a deep, heavy pan over high heat, greasing lightly with shortening. Put in meat and brown thoroughly on all sides.
Cook with the meat 1 package Lipton beefy onion soup mix with liquid.
When meat is a deep, dark brown add tomato juice.
Put on cover and simmer very slowly (about 3 to 4 hours).
During last hour add cut potatoes and carrots.

title: wild west broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until just beginning to soften. In an oven-safe dish, mix all ingredients together, with the exception of 1 tablespoon of butter and the Ritz crackers. Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix in food processor and roll in chopped nuts.
Makes 2 large balls.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix together ingredients; spread on hamburger buns.
Wrap in tinfoil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can also be frozen before baking for later use.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Place in airtight container.
Can be stored up to a week. As needed, spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: moroccan spiced lamb chops(prep  time: 5 minutes; cooking time: 10 minutes.)
directions: Preheat a grill pan over medium-high heat. In a small bowl, combine cumin, turmeric, paprika, coriander, garlic salt and pepper flakes. Brush chops all over with oil; rub spice mixture over both sides of chops to coat. Grill chops, turning once, 9 minutes for medium rare and 11 minutes for medium doneness. Garnish with lemon wedges, if desired. Makes 4 servings; 490 cal., 35 g. fat.

title: michael's marinade
directions: Marinate chicken for a couple of hours or longer if time permits.
Place chicken breast on very hot grill for 20 minutes on each side, brushing remaining marinade on chicken while grilling.

title: sunshine mallow waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, marshmallows, oranges, nuts, raisins and enough salad dressing before serving.
If desired, garnish with apple slices. Serves 8.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Brown chicken parts.
Combine soups, milk and rice and place in baking pan or casserole with a large surface area (9 x 13-inch pan works well).
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover tightly. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Brown rice requires longer cooking. Casserole may be prepared and baked, then refrigerated.
Allow 30 minutes to reheat.

title: marinated salad
directions: Bring to a boil oil, sugar, vinegar, water, salt and pepper. Pour over remaining ingredients.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes and onion in pot. Cover with water. Cook until soft (about 20 minutes). Add butter, milk, salt and pepper.

title: chocolate coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan over low heat.
Add chocolate pieces and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry shells.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before serving.
If desired, top with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crab salad
directions: Stir in dressing mixture and serve cold.
You can use any fresh vegetables.

title: hotch potch
directions: Wash meat; boil in 2 cups water and salt for about 2 hours. Add vegetables and boil until done (about 30 minutes).
Remove meat from pan.
Mash all the vegetables and add butter and pepper. If too thick, add some milk (but a spoon must stand up in it). Serve with the sliced meat.

title: helen's peach pie
directions: Slice 6 or 8 peaches into an uncooked pie shell.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box. Cool cake completely.
Mix pudding mix as directed.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in a punch bowl. Layer 1/2 of the pudding, pineapple, cherry pie filling, Cool Whip and coconut.
Then add all of the chopped pecans.
Then start over with the remaining half of the ingredients.
Keep covered in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: my favorite green beans
directions: Cook bacon in a saucepan until crisp; drain and crumble.
Add green beans.
Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Turn down and simmer for 4 or 5 hours, adding a little water as is necessary, but have sauce pretty thick when you serve them.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain cranberries after grinding.
Add sugar and remaining ingredients.
Add whipped cream last.
Chill and serve.

title: diet soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until done.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in a small amount of oil.
Place in casserole.
Add 1/2 cup water to drippings and pour over meat. Bake covered for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Add whole cored apples and sliced potatoes.
Continue to bake, covered, for 1 hour or until potatoes and apples are done.
Thicken liquid with cornstarch and serve with pork chops.

title: hamburger steaks
directions: Cook pepper, onion and tomato in saucepan with butter until soft.
Pat out 4 large flat patties using half the ground beef and place on broiler pan.
Put equal amount of veggie mixture in center of each patty.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and cheese.
Pat out 4 more patties of hamburger and place on top of mixture, sealing the edges.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute in oleo the onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer for 5 minutes, then add cornstarch. Simmer an additional 3 minutes, then add shrimp. Cook until shrimp are done. Serve over hot rice.

title: shoyu chicken
directions: Mix ingredients with chicken.
Cook 20 minutes and stir.
Cook another 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Cream shortening and oleo.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Crush crackers; mix together.
Mix the cream cheese and sugar.
Mix milk and Dream Whip, then mix cheese and Dream Whip together.
Layer half of crackers in dish.
Layer cream cheese mixture.
Layer blueberries.
Chill and serve.

title: aloha chicken salad
directions: Cook and dice chicken.
Drain fruit well.
Chop celery into fine pieces.
Mix together in large container.

title: pineapple-cherry squares
directions: Spread crumbs evenly in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a small mixer bowl at medium speed, beat butter or margarine until fluffy.
Gradually beat in powdered sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Carefully spread mixture over crumbs.

title: chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in a long Pyrex dish.
Put half slice cheese on each piece.
Mix chicken soup with milk and pour over chicken. Top with Pepperidge crumbs that have been mixed with melted butter.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Drain the green beans.
Place all items in slow cooker on low to medium heat for 4 to 5 hours or in the oven, covered, for 2 hours.
Serve with pork, beef or anything!
So good!

title: superbowl popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
In large roasting pan combine popcorn and pretzels and set aside.
In 2 quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup, and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil (12-14 minutes). Continue cooking until candy thermometer reaches 238° or soft ball stage (4-6 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda. Pour over popcorn and pretzels.
Sprinkle peanuts over caramel mixture.
Stir until all popcorn is coated.
Bake for 20 minutes; stir.
Continue baking for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in candy.
Immediately place caramel corn on wax paper and cool completely.
Break into pieces.
Store in tightly covered container.
Yield:
6 quarts.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop stems; set aside. Drain mushroom tops on paper towels.
Melt butter and add onions, garlic, pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms in frying pan.
Fry until tender (not brown) on lower heat.
Add cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese, parsley, seasoned salt and oregano.
Mix well and add broth.
Spoon stuffing into mushroom.
Place in cake pan with 1/4 cup water and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini goodies
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Mix all ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.
Cut in 2 x 1-inch pieces after cooled. Makes 4 dozen appetizers.
Serve warm.
Freezes well.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Make tea using 1 quart water and 3 tea bags.
Boil together for 5 minutes, sugar, cloves and 2 cups water.
Combine above with tea and orange and lemon juices.

title: * all-in-a-package steak supper *
directions: Place meat on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with soup mix.
Cover with vegetables.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Add water.
Fold over and seal securely to hold in juices.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender. Serves 4.

title: tea scones
directions: Combine
flour,
sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add egg, milk and raisins; mix
well.	Cut
dough
in	half.
Shape each into a ball. Flatten into a 6 inch circle about 1/2 inch thick.	Cut each circle
into
wedges.
Place
on
an ungreased baking sheet. Brush
with the slightly beaten egg.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: refrigerated rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix Crisco, potatoes, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add yeast and potato water which should be cool.
Add flour, 2 cups at a time and knead.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Work down.
May be put in refrigerator and made out into rolls as needed.
Cover with damp towel; take out every day and knead.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together.
Add Cool Whip, strawberries and vanilla flavoring.
Pour mixture into baked shells and chill for several hours.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix in an oblong pan as directed on the box.
While cake is warm, punch holes all over it with the end of a wooden spoon.
Pour bottle of pina colada mix over cake.
Then pour a can of Eagle Brand over the cake.
Top with coconut.
Refrigerate and top with Cool Whip just before serving.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Sift flour and soda together; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased, floured 9 X 13 pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Spread frosting on warm cake.

title: sweet bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out.
Bake like biscuits.

title: heavenly hash
directions: In large bowl, mix Cool Whip and jello.
Drain pineapple, then add to mix.
Add cottage cheese and add nuts last.
Chill for several hours.

title: peanut fingers
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in.
Chill about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Cut cookies in 2 1/2-inch oblong shape.
Bake on greased sheet 2-inches apart for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, dip one end in melted chocolate and then crushed nuts.

title: cheese bran muffins
directions: Mix bran and buttermilk together and set aside.
Mix together all other ingredients and mix with the bran cereal mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: omelet
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Dice pepper and onion.
Drain mushrooms.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Saute all of this together until done.
Add eggs and salt; stir and cook until eggs are done.
Serve hot.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Fork blend egg and oil together.
Dip fish first into the egg mixture, then lightly in crumbs.
Spray nonstick cooking spray onto baking dish.
Arrange fish in single layer.
Salt, pepper and paprika to taste.
Bake in preheated oven at 475° for 10 minutes, without turning.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well.
Put in a 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onion and pepper in jar. Pour mixture over cucumbers (can be hot or cold). Saves for months in refrigerator.

title: copper pennies
directions: Dice pepper and onion and add to cooked, drained carrots. Heat soup, sugar and vinegar to boiling.
Add remaining ingredients to hot mixture and pour over carrots, peppers and onions.
Store covered in refrigerator.
This is better if allowed to set 24 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix and beat well all of the ingredients except the last 3 items.
Sprinkle the box of yellow cake mix on top of mixture. Dribble butter over cake mix.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or longer until crisp and brown.
Serve warm or cold. Can be topped with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: bratwurst with potatoes
directions: Place bratwurst, potatoes and water into wide skillet or saute pan and simmer until water evaporates and the potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Add apples to pan.

title: peach cake
directions: Beat eggs, then add other ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Pour batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream apple crumb
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: coco-not cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and coconut extract.
Add egg and beat.
Stir in Bix-Mix and potato flakes.
Cover bowl and chill for about 1 hour.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello on cottage cheese.
Drain fruit and add to jello mixture.
Stir in whipped topping.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: sauteed egg noodle - cantonese style(panat)
directions: In a stockpot, boil pork and chicken breast in 4 cups of water.
When tender, remove from pot and slice into small pieces, about 1/2-inch strips.
Reserve 3 cups of broth.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers carefully, one at a time.
Any sediment left on can spoil entire batch.
Place in large stoneware crock. Break up dill.
Place among cucumbers. Make brine of water, salt, garlic and spices. Add to cucumbers.
They must be entirely covered with liquid. Cover with an inverted dish weighted down with clean, heavy stone.
Let stand at room temperature until done to your liking.
Length of time will depend on room temperature.
Pickles can be eaten after third or fourth day, but well done pickles must stand a week or longer.
When pickles are to your taste, refrigerate them to halt pickling process.
Yields about 10 quarts.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift
flour,
baking
powder
and salt into medium size bowl. Beat
egg
in
a
small bowl; stir in vegetable oil and water. Pour
over dry ingredients, stirring with a fork until well blended.
Turn
out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Divide
dough
in
half.
Roll
out
each to a 12-inch square,
then
cut them out into 16 (2-inch) squares. Melt enough shortening or pour in enough vegetable oil to make a
2-inch depth in an electric deep fat fryer or heavy saucepan.
Heat
Fry squares 2 or 3 at a time and turning often,
3 to 4 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Serve warm with honey or butter.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll canned rolls and press flat on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes, until crust is all brown.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth; add dressing mix to mixture. Spread mixture on crust.
Top with sliced or chopped vegetables. Add grated cheese last.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend ingredients and beat 4 minutes. Bake according to box directions or until done (when toothpick comes out clean).
Cool 45 minutes on wire rack.

title: beef and chicken dish
directions: Cook chicken, let cool and take off of bones.
Use some of the broth to thin out mushroom soup.
Put 1/2 stick of margarine in pan; add chopped celery, onions and peppers.
Cook until not quite done; cook beef until crumbly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until not quite done.
Cook noodles in boiling water and 1 tablespoon salt.
Do not cook fully done; drain.
Put chicken, beef, noodles, onions, celery, green peppers, mushrooms and olives together and add your mushroom soup, thinned out with some broth from the chicken (not too much).
Mix all together well with noodles.
Grate sharp American cheese; add half to the mixture and put remaining over the top.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chicken kelly
directions: Marinate chicken in eggs for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Combine breadcrumbs, salt, parsley and garlic powder in plastic bag. Shake chicken in breadcrumbs and brown in oil.
Drain and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with a layer of mushrooms and layer of cheese and top with chicken broth.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be made ahead of time, but do not pour chicken broth on until just before baking.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: mixed nut bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread nuts over cooled crust. Melt over low heat the chips, butter and syrup.
Pour over nuts. Bake 10 minutes more.
Cool.
Cut.

title: economy beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into 1/8 inch slices.
Cook and stir beef in butter. Reserve 1/3 cup broth.
Stir the remaining broth, catsup, garlic and salt into skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until beef is tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt, gradually add milk and cook in double boiler over boiling water until thick.
Spoon a small amount of this mixture into the slightly beaten eggs.
Stir and pour back into pudding and cook for about 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Take off burner and add butter and vanilla.
In a glass (9 x 13-inch) Pyrex pan cover bottom with vanilla wafers, then a layer of sliced bananas, then a layer of pudding.
Repeat until all pudding is used.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Wash, scrape carrots and cut into pieces.
Cook in boiling water until just tender.
Drain and cool.
Combine carrots, onion and green pepper in large bowl.
Combine tomato soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour hot mixture over vegetables in bowl.
Cool, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: noodle pudding *
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Melt margarine and cream cheese into hot noodles (in large bowl).
Mix well.
Add eggs, sour cream and sugar.
Stir.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan. Sprinkle corn flakes (crushed) on top, then add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Drizzle 1/3 cup (or little more) milk on top, trying to moisten entire surface.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: one-egg cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Cream until light and fluffy the butter, sugar, vanilla and egg. Stir in half flour mixture, then half of milk; mix well, then add rest of flour mixture and milk.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch square pan, greased and floured.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 25 minutes or test with toothpick near center to see if done.
Frost with Sour Cream Raisin Frosting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften butter and cheese.
Mix and add olives and chives. Roll in nuts.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Slice and put on crackers.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti 15 minutes, drain.
Add next 2 ingredients. Toss in vegetables.

title: texas beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add onion until brown and then beans, bouillon broth and seasonings.
Simmer 60 minutes. Serve over rice and top with condiments.

title: cream of broccoli soup(yield:  6 servings)
directions: In large saucepan, cook broccoli in 1 cup water.
Do not drain.
Put milk, cheese and flour into blender; cover.
Process at grind.
Add mixture to broccoli.
Add half and half.
Cook until thickens.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients (except cheese).
Pour half of mixture into hot greased skillet.
Grate 1 cup cheese over this and add rest of mixture.
Cook at 350° until lightly browned.

title: tennessee barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Melt butter; add onions.
Let simmer for awhile, then add the Worcestershire sauce and let simmer until blended.
Add the lemon juice and let cook slowly.
If desired, Tabasco may be added at this time.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour until thick.
Cool.
Slice bananas in pie shells; sprinkle coconut over bananas, then sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Pour cooled pineapple filling over this.
Top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle top with coconut and finely chopped nuts.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: sweet broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cauliflower in cold water.
Cut up into small bite size pieces including stems.
Blend in sugar, salad dressing and bacon bits.
Add more salad dressing, depending on size of broccoli and cauliflower bunches.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Serve instead of or with potato and macaroni salad or alone.
This is a delicious summer time salad.

title: chicken-rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Start with frozen broccoli and place it in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 7 or 8 minutes to partially thaw.
Stir in Minute rice, chicken, soup and milk.
Stir after each addition. Add 1/2 of cheese and stir in chopped onion.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: sweet and sour carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Dump all in blender and blend until smooth.
Cook pancakes on greased griddle.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain salmon.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll in nuts. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and margarine in a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending on medium speed of mixer.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients (sift together in a smaller bowl) along with milk until all are mixed together.
Cook 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil powdered sugar, margarine and cream four minutes.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Pour into lightly greased pan.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Over medium heat, heat oil in a large pot until hot.
Add onion and garlic, saute for 3 to 5 minutes until the onions begin to appear translucent.
Add the tomatoes, stir to mingle the flavors. Add in the herbs and bay leaf.
Sprinkle in sugar, salt and pepper. Lower the heat and continue to simmer for 30 minutes, uncovered. Stir occasionally.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream the cheese. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Using paper liners in cupcake pans, fill cups 1/8-inch from top.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes until cracks.
Remove from oven.
Cool 5 minutes (will sink, leaving hole).
Mix 1/2 pint sour cream with scant 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Put dash of this mixture on top of each cake (in hole only).
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Cool top with any pie fruit filling.
Blueberry is our favorite!

title: christmas cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream butter.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to butter. Add vanilla and Sucaryl.
Form into a roll.
Wrap roll in wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
When chilled, slice into 24 even sized cookies.
Place on a greased baking sheet in a preheated 350° oven; bake for 15 minutes.

title: guava jelly
directions: Mix juice and Sure-Jell together. Cook to a rolling boil.
Add sugar and stir until melted. Cook until it boils; boil for 3 minutes. Turn off flame. Skim and pour into jars.
Seal.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients together and form about 40 balls.
In oil, cook over low heat for 5 minutes until brown.
Drain off excess oil and mix chili sauce and red jelly together; pour over meatballs.
Let simmer about 10 minutes and serve.
This makes a good appetizer.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Mix Velveeta cheese and butter in saucepan.
Layer broccoli, cheese sauce and crackers.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Make vegetable soup.
Put in potatoes and cook until potatoes are done.
Remove potatoes and mash.
Add egg, milk and flour enough to make stiff dough.
Drop by spoonfuls into soup and steam for 5 minutes, or until dumplings are done.
They will rise to top when done.

title: million dollar dessert
directions: Melt margarine; press flour into melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven until browned.

title: easy pecan cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add 1 cup flour and 1 well beaten egg.
Add 2 cups flour, 1 more well beaten egg and then 1 more cup flour.
Mix well and stir in pecans.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll in logs and wrap in wax paper.
Allow to cool in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Slice and place on a cookie sheet. Bake at 300° until cookies are light brown.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Chunk onion, pepper and cheese. Add rest to blender with 3 tablespoons mayonnaise. Blend.
Fold into remaining mayonnaise.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar; shake well.
Refrigerate for 5 to 7 days.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk, mixing until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened (about 10 minutes).
Add a small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks and mix well.
Add yolk mixture to remaining hot mixture, mixing well.
Cook 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add oleo and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into baked pastry shell and top with meringue.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin.
Cook until tender in salted water.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: In a 3-quart casserole dish place the bread and top with sausage and cheese.
In a medium bowl, combine the eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard, beating well. Pour the mixture over the casserole and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together sugar and oil; add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Add grated carrots. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Ice with whipped cream.

title: good cracker spread
directions: Chop eggs and onion; add pepper.
Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix eggs, onion, pepper and cream cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste with mayonnaise and hot pepper sauce.

title: aunt georgie's peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add peanut butter, eggs and milk.
Add flour mixture.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and peanuts over batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: cracker candy
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Grease with margarine. Place saltine crackers on cookie sheet in a single layer, touching.

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.
Cool and slice into 3 layers.
Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Set aside.
Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until mixed.
Add Dream Whip and mix well.
Frost first layer with icing and then cherry pie filling.
Make sure you use the cherries on the layers.
Do all layers and then frost outside of cake and drizzle filling over the sides.
Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl, one at a time, while the mixer is on. Butter a 10-inch spring-form pan and dust with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour cheesecake mixture into pan and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.
Do not open door!
Let cool in oven for 1 hour with door ajar.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Combine jello and sugar. Dissolve in water. Add pineapple (undrained). Let start to jell in fridge for 15 minutes. Whip topping according to directions. Add softened cream cheese. Mix. Fold in jello mixture. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle pecans over the top.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook the macaroni until tender. Drain and wash. Cut up vegetables.

title: sensational rice
directions: Remove the outer layers from onion and chop into small pieces. Heat oil in skillet and saut onion on medium heat

until soft. Add 1 cup uncooked rice and continue sauteing until the rice begins to brown, stirring constantly (about 10 minutes). Be careful it doesn't burn. Quickly add chicken broth, salt and pepper; reduce heat to simmer. Cover and cook for about 20 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Make a sauce of butter, salt, flour, milk and juice.
Place the last four ingredients in baking dish.
Pour sauce over it and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: surprise carrot cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing until well blended. Set aside.

title: hodge podge soup
directions: Combine ground round, onion, celery, garlic and Worcestershire sauce in large pot.
Cook until meat is done.
Add pork and beans, Ranch Style beans and minestrone.
Add enough water to the desired consistency.
Cook until boiling stage and then it is ready to eat.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir pudding into Cool Whip, then add remaining ingredients. Chill for 2 hours, then serve.

title: veggie bars
directions: Place crescent rolls flat on cookie sheet and brown.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing mix together. Spread over cooled rolls.

title: perfect pretzels
directions: Cut and shape dough into 12 (16-inch) pieces.
Twist pieces into pretzel shape.
Bring water and baking soda to a rapid boil. One at a time, place pretzels into boiling water.
Boil 1 minute. Remove and drain.
Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Brush with egg.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 of cake and put in a large clear glass bowl (small punch bowl).
Add 1/2 of all other ingredients in layers.
Do not mix!
Put other 1/2 crumbled cake and repeat layering other ingredients.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Bring to boil.
Then add sugar. Boil 5 minutes.
Than add 1 bottle Certo.
Return to boil for 5 more minutes.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Makes 8 (8 ounce) jars.

title: apricot bread
directions: Coat 2 baking sheets with cooking spray.
Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Divide in half. Roll each half into size of baking sheet.
Spoon 1/4 cup of fruit spread down the center third of the dough within 1 inch of the ends.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the fresh fruit over the spread.
On the long sides, make 2 inch long cuts from the edges toward the center at 1 inch intervals.
Alternately fold opposite strips of dough, at an angle across fruit filling.
Slightly press the ends together in the center to seal.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until nearly double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove form baking sheets.
Cool slightly.
Drizzle with icing (recipe to follow). Serve warm.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in 375° oven until it is bubbling over the entire casserole.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Combine shortening, butter, sugars, egg and vanilla; mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: calamity
directions: Fry bacon and drain on paper towel. Fry potatoes, onion and green pepper in excess bacon grease. When potatoes are ready, add eggs and spices. Cook until eggs are done. Sprinkle bacon on top and serve.

title: holly candy
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows in saucepan.
Add food coloring and cornflakes and coat well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Add red hot candies for holly berries.
Let stand overnight to firm and dry.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown and drain hamburger, add spaghetti sauce, simmer.
While spaghetti boils, drain spaghetti, mix eggs (beaten).
Put Parmesan cheese on bottom of 3 pie plates.
This is the crust.
Top with cottage cheese, then spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni, bake additional 5 minutes.
Cool and slice.

title: microwave boiled custard
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar to milk and scald 5 minutes on High. Add flour; mix well with remaining sugar. Cook 1 minute on High. Take out and stir. Cook 1 more minute. Stir. Beat egg yolks well. Add 1 cup hot milk to eggs. Mix well. Return to milk mixture. Cook until desired thickness. Stir every 30 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes. Add vanilla flavoring.

title: super chicken casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles.
Cook chicken and cut into small pieces. Saute onions in butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Butter a baking dish; add all ingredients and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and dice.
Add ingredients and bake in greased baking dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: In a large kettle, cook vegetables in melted margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Just before serving, add shrimp and cook until pink.
May add some water, if too thick, or more soup, if too thin.
Serve over rice.

title: potato meat scallops
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add salt and drain.
Melt butter, add flour, stir constantly until thick.
Place alternately beef and potatoes and sauce in greased baking dish.
Cover.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: in place of cream soups
directions: Combine and store in airtight container.
Makes 3 cups. Concentrate is equivalent to 9 (10 1/2 ounce) cans condensed cream soup.

title: whole pork loin sandwiches
directions: Cut the whole pork loins in half to make them easier to handle. Sample the beer. Put each piece (fat side up) on aluminum foil large enough to wrap it up. Sample the beer. Sprinkle with ground pepper, salt and garlic powder. Sample the beer. Squirt with your favorite mustard, 3 or 4 stripes lengthwise. Sample the beer. Wrap with foil and then double wrap. Put in a deep roasting pan. Sample the beer. Cook in 300° oven for 2 to 3 1/2 hours or until center is 180°. Sample many beers; this takes awhile. Unwrap cooked meat but save the juices.

title: milky way cake
directions: Break the Milky Way bars into pieces and put over low heat and let melt.
They will not melt completely. Set aside.
Cream together 1 stick margarine, eggs, sugar and add baking soda, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix all ingredients together with flour. When mixed well, fold in nuts and Milky Way mixture.
Bake in a 10 1/2 x 14-inch greased and floured pan about 45 minutes at

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Season chicken breasts and brown in oleo.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add soup, water and Worcestershire sauce and cook for 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken breasts that have been placed in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until smooth and sugar is dissolved. Add salt and baking soda.
Stir.
Pour mixture over popcorn and stir until all popcorn is coated.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello and pudding mixes with oranges and pineapple.
Stir until there is no sign of dry mixes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Beat until fluffy.
Chill and serve.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend together sugar and flour.
Combine egg yolks and milk. Pour two mixtures together in medium saucepan.
Cook slowly and stir constantly over low heat until mixture becomes thick.
Add butter, flavoring and coconut into mixture and stir until blended. Pour into pie shell.
May top with meringue made of 2 or 3 egg whites, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Garnish with shredded coconut.
Bake until golden brown at 350°
(15 minutes).

title: garlic bread spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread mix 1/4-inch thick on buttered French bread (loaf may be split in half or sliced). Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil until bubbly and serve.

title: canned beans(pickled)
directions: Put
beans
in pan.
Cover with cold water and boil for 25 minutes.
Pack in jars.
Cover with liquid and seal.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer until thick.
Put into jars and seal.
Or simmer until slightly thick, then add a thickener and cold pack for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli mold with almonds(a beautiful ring for a buffet filled with sautéed mushrooms.)
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup salted water until barely tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Chop finely.
Heat butter in a skillet and blend flour, add chicken broth and sour cream gradually.
Stir in green onions and cook over low heat, stirring until thick and blended. Beat eggs lightly and stir into hot sauce.
Cook 1 minute stirring constantly; blend in cheese until melted.
Add broccoli, almonds, and seasonings.
Oil a 1 quart ring mold or 8-5 ounce custard cups. Spoon in mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees in a hot water bath for about 50 minutes for the ring and 30 minutes for the custard cups or until a knife inserted is clean.
Can make ahead and freeze. May be placed in oven frozen, but increase baking time about 30 minutes.

title: steak bake
directions: Place meat in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Toss to coat meat.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: blt salad
directions: For dressing:
Stir mayo, milk, sugar, garlic powder, salt, pepper and onion all together and refrigerate overnight.
(There will be extra dressing).
Stir in large bowl, tomatoes, lettuce, bacon and dressing.
Add croutons and cheese just before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream together margarine and oil. Gradually add sugar and eggs (one at a time).
In separate bowl, mix flour and baking powder.
Alternately add flour mixture with 1 cup of milk to sugar mixture.
Add lemon and vanilla extract. Grease and flour two 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 105 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, chicken, sour cream, chilies and seasonings in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat stirring often until hot. Immediately spoon about 2 tablespoons soup mixture and 1 1/2 tablespoons cheese onto flour tortilla.
Roll up tightly and place in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spoon remaining soup mixture on top of enchiladas and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and scallops stroganoff
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, shell and devein shrimp. Rinse with running cold water.
Pat shrimp and scallops dry. Slice mushrooms.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat and in 2 tablespoons butter, cook shrimp and scallops, stirring frequently, until shrimp turn pink and scallops are tender.
Remove to a bowl.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine the sugar, cooking oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add to combined mixture, 1/2 cup at a time.
Mix well.
Then add carrots.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: six weeks muffins(yield: 60)
directions: Put 2 cups bran into large bowl; pour boiling water over it and let it stand while assembling other ingredients.
Mix in shortening.
Add remainder of bran with sugar, eggs and buttermilk. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Combine all ingredients. Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake desired amount in greased muffin tins or liners at 400° for 20 minutes.
Batter will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl combine egg and 1/4 cup of the soup.
Stir in uncooked rice, onion, parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 20 small balls; place in a 10-inch skillet.
Mix remaining soup with Worcestershire, chili powder and water; pour over meatballs.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes; stir often.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: "can't get enough of that dip"
directions: Crumble, brown and drain hamburger meat.
Add refried beans, red pepper, Velveeta and salsa; heat over low setting.
Stir until mix is smooth.
Pour mixture in serving bowl; put 1/2 carton sour cream in center of mixture (refill as mix goes down,) Dip in chips and enjoy!!!
Ole!

title: dump and taste shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together and taste test.

title: hamburger delight casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck or beef; then add onion, pepper, garlic salt, table salt, sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese.

title: vicki's okra
directions: Wash and slice okra.
Add eggs, cornmeal
and salt and pepper.
Stir to get Okra
coated okra well.
Add oil to skillet and fry over medium heat until tender.

title: ground beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat together with onion and garlic in heavy pan.
Drain any fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Simmer at least one hour.

title: bacon appetizers
directions: Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around cracker.
Place on cookie sheet with overlapping bacon on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until crackers are nicely browned.
Drain quickly on paper towels. Serve while hot.

title: magic nut cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients. Beat together and add the remaining ingredients.

title: oreo mint dessert
directions: Mix the cookie crumbs with 7 tablespoons melted butter.
Press into the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips with 1 tablespoon butter in the microwave.
Beat eggs with an electric mixer.
Slowly add chocolate mixture and beat until thick.
Add powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour over the Oreo layer.
Add liqueur.
Mix well.
Pour over frozen Oreo layer.
Refrigerate.
Remove from freezer and keep in the refrigerator 20 minutes before serving.

title: divinity puffs
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to thin syrup stage.
Slowly pour 1/3 over egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remaining syrup to 234°.
Add one half into egg white mixture, beating constantly. Cook remaining syrup to firm ball stage (248°).
Add to egg white mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture holds shape when dropped from spoon.
Swirl from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Top with English walnut half.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy. Flavor with love and kindly service; fold in 4 cups prayer and faith; blend well; fold in daily life.
Bake well with human kindness and serve with a smile anytime.
It will satisfy the hunger of starved souls.
This is great for those in between snacks, also.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: beefy nachos
directions: In a large skillet, over medium-high heat, brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in steak sauce.
Arrange tortilla chips on a large heat-proof platter.
Spoon beef mixture over chips; sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 6 inches from heat source, for 3 to 5 minutes. Top with sour cream, tomato, chilies and olives.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti sauce(italian style)
directions: "And prepare for me savory food, such as I love, and bring it to me that I may eat."
Genesis 27:4

title: date pudding
directions: Beat all together and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: egg custard pie(instant crust)
directions: Melt margarine in cake pan at 400°.
Beat eggs; add sugar and flour and mix.
Add vanilla and milk and mix.
Add butter from pan and mix.
Pour in pan where margarine was melted.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Finish baking at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean and pie is golden brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a mixing bowl and blend with mixer, slowly adding whipping cream until smooth. Spoon filling into pie shell. Top peanut butter filling with frosting.

title: brunswick stew
directions: You can saute the the onion and meat.
Combine the remaining ingredients and put in crock-pot.
Cook slow 1/2 day at least.

title: lite-delight strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until gelatin is thickened, about 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whisk, blend in Cool Whip, then whip until smooth.
Fold in strawberries.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream, ice cream or Cool Whip, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; form into small balls and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 5 dozen.
