title: blueberry cheese supreme
directions: Mix together crumbs, flour and butter; press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; let cool and set aside. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip together with mixer until well blended.
Pour into cooled crust and let set up for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with 1 can pie filling (may use any type of pie filling).

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening together.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well, then add oatmeal, Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts.
If mixture is too dry, add 1 tablespoon of water.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: anna's old-fashioned apple stack cake
directions: Mix milk, sugar, molasses, oil, eggs, vanilla and flour. Divide batter into 5 equal parts to make 5 thin layers.
Put into greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° until done.
Cool.

title: snickers bars
directions: Pour one package of chocolate chips in a 9 x 13-inch pan and melt in the microwave.
Spread chocolate over bottom of pan.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Place yeast in warm water.
Melt oleo; cream sugar in large bowl, then add beaten egg.
Add dissolved yeast mixture.
Add flour and stir well.
Place in airtight bowl and keep in refrigerator. Fill muffin tin a little over half full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: jambalaya
directions: Place spareribs on broiling rack and bake at 400° until brown; set aside.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Pour Jello over cottage cheese and toss.
Add pineapple, nuts, and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Garnish top with more nuts, if desired.
Any flavor of Jello may be used.

title: speedy salad
directions: Fold cream into pudding.
Drain fruit cocktail, oranges and cherries.
Fold fruit into pudding.
Add mini marshmallows and bananas.
Chill.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Dice onion, green pepper and celery. Blend sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour sugar and oil mixture over all other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Drain to serve.
Keeps a long time in refrigerator.

title: coconut pecan bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients together except paraffin and chocolate. Shape into small balls and refrigerate for about 30 minutes.
Using double boiler, melt paraffin.
Then melt the chocolate into paraffin.
Using toothpicks, dip refrigerated balls into chocolate paraffin mixture.
Place on wax paper.
Makes approximately 90.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and Karo 4 minutes on High; stir.
Add peanuts, cook 4 minutes on High.
Add vanilla and butter, cook 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Stir in soda.
Pour at once on buttered pan and spread.
Cool and break in pieces.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Beat in large bowl. Add sausage. Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish; let stand several hours (can be overnight or frozen). Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Cut in squares.

title: butterless, eggless, milkless cake
directions: Boil brown sugar, 1 1/4 cups water, shortening, raisins and spices together for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add salt and baking soda, which has been dissolved in 2 teaspoons water.
Gradually add the flour and baking powder, which have been sifted together, beating smooth after each addition.
Bake in a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan in a moderate (325°) oven about 50 minutes or until done.
Needs no frosting.

title: chicken and rice mexican
directions: In Dutch oven, heat oil until hot.
Add chicken (brown on all sides).
Drain off excess fat.
Add broken up tomatoes, water, chili powder, salt, oregano and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Stir rice and corn into chicken.
Cover and bake an additional 10 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Soften yeast in water.	Mix all ingredients, except egg and salt.
Knead dough and shape into 12 large or more smaller pretzels.
Brush
with
egg
and sprinkle with salt.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tasty apple treats
directions: For each sandwich, spread one bagel half with 1 teaspoon preserves.
Top with process cheese food and apple.
Dot with remaining preserves.
Broil until process cheese food begins to melt.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: sunset cake
directions: Combine pudding mix, cake mix and gelatin.
Add oil and milk, beating well.
Beat in eggs.
Bake in 3 greased 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Cool completely.
In mixing bowl, combine sour cream, powdered sugar, pineapple and coconut, blending well.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Spread remaining mixture between layers.
Fold together reserved pineapple mixture and whipped topping.
Frost top and sides of cake.
Store cake in covered container in refrigerator.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables with turkey ham and pour into a baking dish. Place cheese on top and bake at 325° until cheese is melted.

title: vegetable pancakes
directions: Grate carrots and zucchini.
Slice scallions.
Combine flour, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Beat together egg, milk, carrots, zucchini and scallions.
Stir wet ingredients into dry until just combined.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend together all ingredients.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheets and bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, baking powder and soda; set aside.
In large mixer bowl beat butter and sugars until light.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Gradually stir n flour mixture, then coarsely chopped Andes, (optional walnuts and raisins).
Drop onto ungreased baking sheets by tablespoonfuls.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until cookies brown.
Cool on sheets 2 to 3 minutes. For thicker cookies refrigerate dough 15 to 20 minutes before cooking.

title: italian wedding cakes
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Dough will be soft.
Drop from a teaspoon onto greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cookies do not need to be brown.
Cool.

title: crunch and munch
directions: Cook Karo syrup, margarine and brown sugar over medium heat, for 5 minutes.
Then add cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Mix well, and then pour over the popped popcorn and peanuts.
Then bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Mix together Oreo cookies and melted oleo; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, 1 Cool Whip and powdered sugar; spread over cookie layer.
Prepare chocolate instant pudding with milk and layer into pan.
Spread 1 Cool Whip over pudding layer.
Sprinkle with crumbled cookies, if desired.

title: lemon-berry freezer pie
directions: Put crackers in plastic bag and crush.
Mix crumbs with melted margarine and sugar and put in 9-inch pie plate on bottom and up sides.
Refrigerate for 45 minutes or freeze for 15 minutes until crust is firm.

title: world's best cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg; mix well.
Add oil and vanilla; mix well.
Add oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well.
Add four, soda and salt.
Mix well.

title: glazed apricot chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dressing, preserves and soup mix. Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; pour dressing mixture over chicken.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam. Core and quarter

peeled apples. Wrap each quarter with rectangle of crescent roll. Place in baking dish. Mix sugar, juice, butter and cinnamon in pot and heat until butter is melted. Pour over apples and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When done, spoon hot mixture over apples. Makes 8 dumplings.

title: velvet chocolate sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, cook and stir sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Add chocolate chips and butter or margarine.
Stirring frequently over medium heat, cook until smooth.
Stir in corn syrup.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Serve warm over ice cream or dessert of your choice.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator.
Reheat before using.
Sauce will keep for a long time.
Makes about 2 1/3 cups.

title: deviled crab meat
directions: Make white sauce in double boiler with first 4 ingredients; add celery and onion.
Gently fold in crab meat, bread crumbs and hard-boiled egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole; top with buttered crumbs and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: tammie's special biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar thoroughly.
Pour oil into milk and mix.
Preheat oven to 450°. Brush cooking pan with butter before putting in hot oven.
Cook until brown on top and bottom.

title: seven layer dip
directions: On a large round platter, spread sour cream, top with mashed avocados, sprinkle dry taco seasoning over avocados, top with picante sauce, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, then tomatoes. Garnish with tostada chips.

title: the "100" cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar; set aside.
Mix together white and brown sugars, margarine, oil, egg, vanilla, Rice Krispies, coconut and oats.
Blend in flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool on pan a few minutes before removing.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion and green pepper; simmer.
Cook egg noodles.
Drain both and combine all ingredients into a large bowl, except cheese and pepperoni. Pour into a baking dish and cover with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: apple nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix the dry ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until the edges are golden.
Remove from oven and cut into bars while still warm, not hot.

title: bacon, lettuce, cauliflower salad
directions: Shred the lettuce and cut up cauliflower into salad size pieces.
Fry or microwave bacon crispy.
Crumble bacon.
Combine all ingredients in salad bowl; add mayonnaise to taste.
Toss and wa laa!

title: fried chicken and gravy
directions: Stir the salt and pepper, egg and flour by hand.
Lay chicken in prepared skillet that is hot enough with oil, shortening or lard (lard is best) to begin frying.
Fry slowly until chicken is brown. Add gravy.

title: mildred gregory's crumb cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients listed until crumbly.
Take out 1/2 cup of crumbs for topping.
Beat egg, buttermilk and soda separately in a bowl.
Combine the beaten mixture and crumb mixture together.
(Do not add topping to this mixture!)
Put in a greased pan and put the 1/2 cup of crumb mixture on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and butter.
Add egg, juice and cranberries.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients; combine with egg mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Shape into rolls or squares 2-inches wide.
Wrap in aluminum foil or waxed paper and chill overnight or freeze.
Slice thin and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for about 12 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: goulash
directions: Fry ground meat in skillet; drain fat. Mix all ingredients in ovensafe baking dish. Add meat. Mix well. Put in oven, preheated to 350°. Heat for 15 minutes. Serve.

title: country potato gratin
directions: Rub garlic clove inside entire oval casserole dish.
Butter dish.
Place 1/4 potatoes in pan, covering with 1/4 Gruyere, ground nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Layer next 1/4 of potatoes, repeating until all potatoes are in pan.
Leave off last 1/4 of Gruyere.
In pan, beat egg until foamy.
Add scalded milk in slow, steady stream, whisking constantly.
Pour custard over potatoes.
Cover with remaining cheese.

title: shrimp canapes
directions: Chop shrimp, add mayonnaise, onion and seasonings, mixing well.
Cut strips of cheese to fit Club crackers, top each one with 1 tablespoon of mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (optional).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy sausage balls
directions: Grate
cheese;	combine with Bisquick and sausage.
Mix well; add hot sauce and black pepper.
Mix thoroughly (mixture is stiff).
Pinch
off
quarter
size pieces; roll into balls. Do not flatten.
Place
on
ungreased
baking sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° approximately 15 minutes or until brown.

title: mexican fried chicken
directions: Mash garlic and 1/2 teaspoon of salt until pasty.
Rub chicken with mixture.
Arrange chicken in a shallow dish and sprinkle with lime juice and onion.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours, turning meat occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade and pat dry.

title: french potato salad
directions: In medium saucepan, cook potatoes covered in 2 inches boiling water, just until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool potatoes.
In large bowl, whisk oil, vinegar, water, mustard and pepper.
Mix in onions, parsley and tarragon.
Add potatoes; toss lightly to coat.
Season with salt.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in microwave-safe bowl. Cook in microwave for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and microwave 3 minutes.
Stir and microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir in margarine, vanilla and baking soda.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break apart.

title: microwave rice krispies treats
directions: Microwave margarine and marshmallows on High 2 minutes in microwave-safe mixing bowl.
Stir to combine microwave on High 1 minute longer.
Stir until smooth.
Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.

title: cheesey spinach
directions: Pre-cook fresh spinach for about 5 minutes. Drain. Mix together the soup, cheese and spinach in mixing bowl. Put mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and cover top with croutons. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes. Serves 12.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion and margarine in microwave.
Add to mixture of squash, cornbread and cream of chicken soup.
Mix well.
Pour in 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spanish meatballs(albondigas)
directions: Combine meat, salt, nutmeg and parsley in a large bowl. Squeeze water from bread and add bread and egg to meat mixture. Form into 36 small balls.
In a frying pan, heat olive oil and saute meatballs until thoroughly cooked and brown (about 20 minutes).
Serve immediately.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and butter. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs.
Pour onto cake mix. Bake at 325° or 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into squares while still warm.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Cream together softened cream cheese and butter. Add vanilla. Add sugars and chips, mix well. Refrigerate for 2 hours. Roll into 2 balls, put back in refrigerator for another hour. Roll in chopped pecans. Serve with graham crackers and or vanilla wafers. If made with low fat cream cheese the results will be more like dip consistency rather than a firm ball.

title: rolo cookies
directions: Melt together margarine, Eagle Brand milk and chocolate chips. Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Top each cookie with a Rolo candy.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: one, two, three, four cake
directions: Add baking powder and salt to four.
Cream shortening; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Beat in flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.
This may be used for a sheet cake with frosting of your choice or baked in a tube pan with or without frosting.

title: quick brunswick stew
directions: I use Castleberry pork and beef, and Sweet Sue chicken.
Use all cans undrained.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer for few minutes until hot.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend milk with hand mixer or wire whisk.
Add lemonade. Blend.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add yellow food coloring (optional). Pour into pie shell.
Keep pie in the freezer.
Garnish with sliced lemon.
Be sure to bake pie shell first.

title: sandy's broccoli soup
directions: Brown chopped onion in oleo.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes; bring to boil.
Add noodles and salt.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Add garlic powder and milk.
Bring to boil; add Velveeta cheese.
When cheese is melted, add broccoli. Makes 1 gallon.

title: e-z cobbler
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and milk until blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add fruit pie filling to batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: my pound cake
directions: Cream oleo with sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs and flour mixture with sour cream, small amounts at a time, until blended. Last, add flavorings.
Bake in a 10-inch mold for 1 hour and 30 minutes (about) at 350° until tested with toothpick.

title: apple muffins
directions: Stir thoroughly first 5 ingredients.
Make well in center. Blend egg, milk, oil and apple; pour into well of the dry mixture. Stir just until moistened.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full. Sprinkle with mixture of the 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: frozen pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order:
cherry pie filling, pineapple, milk, whipped topping, marshmallows and pecans.
Spoon into a 2 1/2-quart mold and freeze.
Then unfold if desired.
For individual servings, line muffin tins with cupcake liners; fill and freeze.

title: tomatoes stuffed with chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt, pickle, and mayonnaise; chill. Cut tops off of tomatoes.
Scoop a little of the centers out.
Cut 6 slices almost through tomatoes.
Spread into flower shape, and place on lettuce.
Stuff with chicken salad.
Garnish with sliced eggs and olives.

title: cornbread
directions: In large bowl mix ingredients, then add 6 cups boiling water, cover and let sit overnight or a few hours.
Bake at 375° in large 14 x 10-inch greased pan for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: banana salad
directions: Blend and cook milk, sugar and flour on medium heat until it just thickens.
Just as it comes to a boil, take off heat and add 1 tsp. butter.
Cool.
Then add 1 Tbsp. mayonnaise.
Layer bananas, peanuts and this dressing.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in an oblong pan.
Place in pan, in following order, graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and pecans. Drizzle milk over mixture and bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: microwave salmon ring
directions: Combine all ingredients except creamed peas in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix well.
Move mixture from center to form ring. Place a dish in center (small glass dish) to form ring.
Cook uncovered in microwave for 8 minutes or until salmon is set. Remove dish and fill with creamed peas.

title: coke salad
directions: Bring pineapple juice and cherry juice to boil.
Dissolve jello in boiling juice.
Blend in softened cream cheese with a fork or blend with small amount of jello mixture.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in mold and let jell, the longer it stays the better.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook the macaroni according to box directions. Drain and rinse.
Add the chopped vegetables and the cleaned, chunked shrimp. Add mayonnaise to reach a desirable consistency and season to your taste.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Saute sausage, onion, bell pepper and chicken with seasoning in large skillet with 2 tablespoons butter until sausage is done, then add dirty rice mix.
Mix well and let simmer for about 25 minutes.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, water and sugar.
Add oil, whole wheat flour, caraway seeds, salt and flour.
Beat until smooth. Let rise. Punch down.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead.
Pinch off 3 small balls and place in greased muffin tins.
Makes about 18 to 20 rolls. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg, lemon juice and well mashed bananas.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Then stir in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Very moist.

title: ham & cheese roll-ups
directions: Roll cheese & ham together into shape of log.
Serve with pickles.
Enjoy.

title: peanut butter s'mores
directions: Place 1 peanut butter cup on each of 4 crackers.
Spear marshmallows on a long fork or clean stick; toast over campfire coals or grill on low heat.
Place one toasted marshmallow on top of each peanut butter cup; top each with a cracker.
Press together and hold for a few seconds to melt chocolate and serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: fudge brownie ring
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 325° in a Bundt pan (greased and floured).
Test with toothpick for doneness.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Turn out onto plate.
Sift powdered sugar over top and serve.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients and stir.
Add carrots, apples, raisins and nuts; stir well.
Make a well in the center and add rest of ingredients (liquid).
Stir just until moistened.
Use 1/4 cup measure to scoop into greased muffin tins. Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except parsley and pecans. Combine parsley and pecans and blend half of them into cheese mixture.
Spread remaining parsley mixture on sheet of waxed paper. Form cheese into a ball and roll it in parsley mixture until well coated.
Chill before serving.
May be made long before serving. Freezes beautifully.
Approximate yield:
4 (11 1/2 ounce) balls.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Pat in a 10 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding with milk. Pour over top; let cool several hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham fat side up in shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours (10 minutes per pound) to internal temperature of 130°.
One hour before end of baking time, cut fat into diamond shapes; stud with cloves.
Pour glaze over ham.
Place pineapple slices over top of ham; insert cherry into center of hole of pineapple slices, securing with toothpick. Return to oven for 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.
Remove ham from oven and let stand 15 to 20 minutes for easier carving.

title: play doh
directions: Place all ingredients into saucepan and mix.
Add food coloring last.
Cook over low heat and stir until play doh begins to pull away from the sides of the pot and forms a ball.
Remove from heat, cool and store in airtight container.

title: favorite hot chocolate
directions: Combine dry ingredients in saucepan.
Blend in water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly; boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add milk; stir and heat.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; beat with rotary beaters until foamy.
Makes 1 quart.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 inch baking pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake according to package directions at 350°.
Batter will be thick.

title: green beans, potatoes with bacon and mushrooms
directions: In a large kettle with a lid or a Dutch oven, place bacon pieces and onion slices. Over medium heat, cook until bacon is lightly brown and onion is crisp-tender. Add green beans, potatoes, water, salt and pepper; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until potatoes will break when pierced with a fork. Drain liquid from potatoes, reserving 1 1/2 cups of the liquid and return to the potatoes in the kettle. Add canned soup and sliced mushrooms. Stir gently to blend. Return to
medium-low heat for 5 to 8 minutes, covered. Remove from heat and allow to stand about 20 minutes for flavors to marry. Serves 8.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with cracker crumbs.
Reserve one cup for later.
Slice bananas into rounds and layer over crust.
Slice ice cream into one inch thick slices and place over bananas.
Sprinkle nuts on ice cream.
Freeze until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Add powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook until thick stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool.
Pour over ice cream and freeze until firm. Whip cream stiff.
Spread over chocolate layer and top with crumbs.
Store in freezer.
Remove 10 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add Miracle Whip to suit your taste.

title: ginger ale pie
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Melt vanilla ice cream into 1 cup heated ginger ale.
Combine the 2 liquids and refrigerate until it begins to thicken.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar well; add applesauce and mix in the dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured 8-inch cake pan or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until done, slightly longer if in loaf pan.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, sour cream and dry ingredients.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 1 hour and 20 or 30 minutes at 325°.

title: marinated turkey breast
directions: Place turkey in browning bag and place in shallow roasting pan.
Combine parsley, olive oil, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Pour over turkey.
Seal bag and bake at 300° for 4 to 5 hours.
Cut several slits in top of bag before placing in oven.
Serve hot with thickened pan drippings.
Drippings can be thickened with a small amount (1 to 2 tablespoons) cornstarch mixed with water.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix soda in the milk; put in the oats.
Put in the raisins; sift the flour with the baking powder and spices.
Drop by large spoon on greased pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown.

title: quick fish soup
directions: Cook and stir onions and garlic in oil in Dutch oven, or heavy saucepan, until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer until fish flakes easily, about 5 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion together.
Add the vegetables to the bacon mixture.
Cook until the vegetables are tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add milk and simmer for 1/2 hour or so.

title: strawberry slush
directions: In a large bowl, mash strawberries; add ice cream. In a small bowl, dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in lemon juice.
Add to the strawberry mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart freezer container; cover and freeze overnight.
Remove from the freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Spoon into glasses; add soda.
Garnish with strawberries if desired.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: creamy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese
at
high
speed
with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add
whipped
topping, peanut butter, sugar and milk; beat well.
Spoon
half
of
mixture into crust; drizzle with chocolate
syrup.
Carefully
top with remaining filling. Drizzle additional syrup
on top, sprinkle on chopped peanuts. Chill at least 5 hours before serving.

title: scottish tea scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine bread crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with fork.
Divide in two parts and turn each part out on floured board.
Do not handle.
Flatten with rolling pin into circles about 1/2-inch or more thick.
Cut in triangles and put on greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm, slightly buttered. Yield:

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Beat until smooth. Add milk and corn.
Place in greased casserole.
Drop butter on top.
Bake in oven at 350°.
Stir after 30 minutes and continue baking for 20 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop corn.
Place in big brown paper bag.
In large glass microwavable bowl, place all ingredients, except baking soda, which goes in after coating is cooked.
Place in microwave for 5 minutes.
Stir after 2 1/2 minutes, then finish cooking.
After 5 minutes is up, stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda immediately.
Stir quickly, it may foam up, this is okay.
When completely stirred in, pour over popped corn and stir in.
Place brown bag in microwave for 1 minute.
Stir and then cool.

title: salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Mash tomatoes with hands to mush up.
Chill.

title: knox blocks
directions: In a large bowl, combine Knox unflavored gelatine, Jell-O and water.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour in jelly roll pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into pieces.
Can be cut with cookie cutters.

title: mock toffee
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with foil, then spray with vegetable oil. Arrange one layer of saltines on the bottom of the pan. Combine the butter and brown sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Stir cautiously for about 3 minutes, being careful not to burn. Pour the sugar mixture over the crackers and spread evenly. Bake for 20 minutes. Remove from the oven and pour the chocolate chips over the sugar mixture. Wait 1 minute for the chips to melt, then spread evenly. Sprinkle the pecans evenly over the chocolate. Let cool and cut with a pizza cutter or break into pieces to serve. Makes about 20 pieces.

title: coconut custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pie pan. Makes own crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour on top of butter.
Do not stir.
Pour pie filling on top of dough.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except milk and eggs.
Add them last. Bake in a greased loaf pan in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters; set aside.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a flat pan or dish.
Place each quarter of biscuit into mixture, covering well.
In a greased Bundt pan, press all biscuit pieces firmly into place, starting at bottom and layering upwards. Combine melted butter and leftover cinnamon-sugar mixture into pot on the stove.
Simmer until dissolved.
Pour hot mixture through biscuits.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, or until fluffy. Serve warm.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Place yeast, water and 1 tablespoon of sugar in a large bowl; set aside.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Heat buttermilk on low heat until lukewarm.
Combine with yeast mixture.
Add remaining sugar and corn oil; mix well.
Add flour mixture, 2 cups at a time; blend.
Let stand for 10 minutes; knead for 5 minutes.
Form into rolls; place on greased pans or 3 small pieces into cups of muffin pans for cloverleaf rolls.
Brush tops with melted margarine.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken and chop into bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli for 7 minutes and drain.
Add all ingredients, except for stuffing and broth, in large mixing bowl and mix well.
Add 1 box of stuffing mix (chicken flavor) and enough chicken broth for soft casserole.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine
all ingredients together into a ball.	Roll in chopped pecans and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, slice and 1/4-inch thick.
In large iron skillet, put enough oil to fry potatoes.
Place potatoes in hot oil, a few at a time.
Fry like French fries; some will puff up. Most will float when done.
Cook to a golden brown.
May need turning.
Good when sprinkled with powdered sugar or syrup poured over them.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add the above ingredients in 1 pkg. orange jello.

title: majestic peanut butter cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and peanuts, stirring to mix.
Add melted margarine, stirring to mix.
Press mixture on bottom and up sides to top of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Place peanut butter and vanilla in a large mixing bowl and cream with electric beaters.
Add cream cheese and beat at medium speed of electric mixer until thoroughly mixed.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together by hand in a large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Combine soups with margarine in dish.
Add rice.
Bake in casserole dish for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled turnips(lifit)
directions: Quarter or half turnips, depending on size. Put in a quart jar and add salt.
Mix the water and vinegar and pour solution over the turnips to cover.
Seal loosely and let sit for a week until serving.

title: pink vodka sauce for pasta
directions: Saute onion in olive oil and butter until transparent.
Add tomatoes and simmer for approximately 25 minutes on low heat.
Add cream, vodka and red pepper.
Heat until warm; do not bring to a boil.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light. Add sugar and vanilla and beat well. Pour egg mixture and all other ingredients into a 1 gallon freezer and freeze.
Makes about 1/2 gallon.

title: broccoli cheese and chicken casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine water, contents of seasoning packet and rice.
Stir well.
Stir in chicken and broccoli.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 400° and continue baking for 25 minutes more.
Sprinkle top of casserole with cheese and bread crumbs.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all and put in a roaster pan.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours or at 300° for 3 hours.

title: icy fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Add drained fruit, marshmallows and cherries.
Stir well.

title: spicy percolator punch
directions: Mix juices, water and sugar in the percolator.
Put cinnamon sticks and spices in the basket.
Perk as for coffee.
Serve hot. Yield: 6 to 10 cups.

title: stew
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix in heavy 5 to 6-quart Dutch oven, tomatoes, wine or water, beef broth, tapioca, sugar, herbs, salt, bay leaves and pepper.
Stir in beef.
Add carrots, celery and onions.
Stir and bake 3 hours, stirring twice, until meat is tender and sauce is thickened.
discard bay leaves before serving or refrigerating.

title: cupa, cupa, cupa
directions: Mix together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 45 minutes at 350° and enjoy.

title: one good cookie
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: donut muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together well.
Add egg and milk. Add flour, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Melt in a saucepan the margarine or butter.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon together in a small bowl.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until muffins are done.
When slighlty cooled, dip tops of muffins in the butter or margarine and then into the sugar/cinnamon mixture.

title: it's good chicken
directions: Saute onions in butter. Add soup and mushrooms.
Mix and pour over chicken in a casserole dish. Top with Cheddar cheese and bake until bubbly. Serve over noodles.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat together margarine and sugar with a spoon.
Beat in egg, oil and vanilla.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Stir into margarine mixture.
Chill dough 1 hour or until easy to handle.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten to 1/4-inch with the tines of a fork, dipping fork in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes. Makes 40 cookies.

title: cousin rosalind's scones
directions: Mix all ingredients together; turn out onto floured surface. Shape as you would biscuits; bake for 12 minutes at 450°.
Makes about 13 scones.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve with slices of apples, oranges, pineapple or strawberries.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place pie crust on bottom of dish and bake. Mix together peaches (with syrup), sugar, nutmeg, butter and vanilla. Pour into baked crust. Cover top with another crust or strips of crust. Sprinkle top with sugar. Bake at 350° until done.

title: sweet and spicy mixed nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Lightly spray a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with nonstick vegetable coating.
Set aside.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients in large bowl until fluffy.
With mixer on low, gradually beat in flour just until blended.
Divide dough into thirds.
Shape each into 10-inch long roll.
Wrap and freeze 12 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Slice frozen dough in 1/4-inch thick rounds, place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until light brown.

title: aunt libby's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Spry, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, soda, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients, mixing with a spoon (NOT A MIXER).
Pour into three 8-inch round pans (wax paper lined).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: lite raisin cream pie
directions: Simmer raisins and water 5 to 7 minutes.
Beat egg yolks, sugar and flour until light and creamy.
Carefully and slowly add to raisins.
Cook, stirring constantly, until filling thickens, 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add margarine and cool slightly. Pour into shell.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine all vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into dish.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Add beef, onion and garlic. Cook until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika, mustard, cayenne and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Boil until tender.
Drain.
Saute onion, garlic, parsley, celery and meat until the meat changes color.
Add eggplant, milk and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour in baking dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: Mix cake batter according to package directions.
Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: deviled crab
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Beat eggs with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add crab meat, crumbs and milk.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: ed's concoction chili
directions: In large stock pan, place oil and heat on medium heat.
Add meat, onion, celery and garlic.
Cook until meat is browned and onions are clear.
Add all ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil. Turn down heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: cornbread dumplings
directions: In mixing bowl, add corn meal and salt.
Slowly add enough water to make a medium-soft dough.
(More water if you like soft dumplings and less if you like hard ones.)
Pat 2 or more tablespoons of the dough between both hands.

Place in a pot of cooking greens, chicken or whatever you want to put dumplings in. After they cook for about 12 minutes on top of greens, stir further down and let cook about 10 to 12 minutes longer.

title: sweet and salty
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add peanuts and pretzels.
Stir until coated.
Pour and spread onto wax paper.
After mixture hardens, break into pieces.

title: basic crepes
directions: Having a stock of crepes on hand in your freezer can be a life-saver at times.
In an emergency, you can turn out a gourmet dish in a jiffy.
Fill with almost anything and top with a good sauce and with a salad the meal is a success.

title: butter roll(old time dessert)
directions: *One half milk and 1/2 canned milk makes it creamier.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and set aside.
Brown chops.
Spread potatoes in a baking dish and lay chops on top.
Pour in soup and milk.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until chops and potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, drain off excess fat.
Add beans, mustard, ketchup, brown sugar and onion.
Mix well.
Pour into a baking dish.
Lay bacon strips over top of beans.
Place into 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: no cook noodles lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add sauce.
Put some sauce on bottom of pan, then layer of noodles.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese, then layer with sauce and noodles.
Alternate layers again.
Top with sauce, then Mozzarella cheese.
Pour hot water in and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: escalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions in 1 tablespoon margarine. Melt remaining 4 tablespoons of margarine in a large saucepan.
Add flour, stirring until completely dissolved.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Stir continuously until all ingredients are blended and mixture begins to thicken.
Add sauteed onions, potatoes and ham with the thickened sauce; stir gently to combine.
Place mixture into greased casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs. Place casserole on cookie sheet or in a baking pan to prevent spillage during baking.
Bake until it begins to bubble around the edges, approximately 40 to 50 minutes.

title: salt pickles
directions: Bring to boil and pour over cold cucumbers packed in sterilized jars setting in boiling hot water.
Seal immediately. Leave sitting in hot water to make sure they seal.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt cream cheese over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into ovenproof dish and bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: herbed chicken with vegetables
directions: Preheat grill for 10 minutes.
In 8-inch square grill safe baking dish, combine celery, mushrooms, tomato, butter, salt, basil and pepper.
Stir.
Place dish on cooking grid.
Arrange chicken bone side down on cooking grid beside vegetables. Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt.
Grill at medium with hood closed for 5 minutes.
Turn chicken over and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Stir vegetables.
Grill with hood closed for 5 minutes longer.
Arrange chicken on vegetables.
Cover.
Bake using indirect medium heat with hood closed until meat near the bone no longer is pink, about 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; remove all skin, bones and fat.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Add vegetables.
Mix broth and soup together; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and milk. Put chicken mixture in bake dish.
Pour batter over top; slice margarine and place on top of batter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°, or until dough is done.

title: french apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease pie plate.
Mix apples and spices; turn into plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Top with Streusel.

title: vogler barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours; cool.
After cooking brisket, slice 1/2 to 1-inch thick. Pour sauce over meat; place in heavy-duty foil before adding sauce.
Wrap securely; place on low coals for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve.

title: biscuit doughnuts
directions: Heat oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Using doughnut cutter, cut holes in biscuits.
Drop into deep fryer until golden brown. Remove and drain on paper towels.
Cool about 2 minutes and roll in powdered sugar.
Serve warm or cold.

title: snookerdoodles (cookies)
directions: Make well in cake mix; add eggs and oil.
Stir well.
Add Jack Daniels and mix well.
Dough will be thick (stiff).
Make balls; roll in powdered sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
If you like, put half a walnut or pecan or glaced cherry in center. Cook at 350° for about 15 minutes or until done.
Makes about 55 cookies.

title: pecan chicken salad
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Pour 3 cups chicken broth (your choice preparation) over and bake at 350° until done.
